1
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:16,840
<i>The legendary search</i>
<i>for the next top models and actors</i>

2
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:21,440
that reshaped the Thai entertainment
and fashion industries is back.

3
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:25,680
Join me, Kim Goodburn,
on this historic new journey.

4
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:28,600
And this is
<i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4.</i>

5
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:37,160
<i>The return of the number one</i>
<i>reality phenomenon, </i>The Face Thailand<i>.</i>

6
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:41,080
<i>The reality show that dominates</i>
<i>every platform, every season.</i>

7
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:45,640
<i>This is the new journey</i>
<i>of </i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4<i>.</i>

8
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,520
<i>With a mission to find the one gentleman</i>

9
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,960
<i>who'll step up</i>
<i>as a professional model and actor.</i>

10
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:54,040
<i>Thailand's fourth </i>The Face Men<i>.</i>

11
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,840
<i>The winner of</i>
The Face Men Thailand Season 4

12
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:30,440
<i>will collaborate with Clear Thailand.</i>

13
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:34,280
<i>He will receive a one-year supply</i>
<i>of Clear Ice Cool Menthol.</i>

14
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,880
<i>And get the chance to work</i>
<i>with Vaseline Thailand.</i>

15
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:40,520
<i>Plus, he'll receive</i>
<i>Vaseline SPF50+ PA++++,</i>

16
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,920
<i>Gluta Hyaluronic Acid,</i>
<i>Photoage Defense UV Serum</i>

17
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,720
<i>free for an entire year.</i>

18
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,000
<i>He will also collaborate with AXE.</i>

19
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:51,160
<i>And receive a year's supply</i>
<i>of personal care products.</i>

20
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:54,640
<i>Bearbeary: Only the wearers feel it.</i>

21
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:58,520
<i>Premium wear for every style,</i>
<i>featuring top design and innovation.</i>

22
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,760
<i>They'll award a 100,000-baht gift voucher.</i>

23
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:04,920
<i>Strive for perfection</i>
<i>with a membership to Hotman Fitness.</i>

24
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,760
<i>Including an 18-month</i>
<i>personal training program.</i>

25
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:11,760
<i>Plus a 200,000-baht package</i>
<i>from V Design Clinic.</i>

26
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:14,360
<i>Get ready to step onto the national screen</i>

27
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:17,400
<i>through a collaboration</i>
<i>with Channel 3 HD, Thailand.</i>

28
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:21,280
<i>And sign an acting contract</i>
<i>with Kantana Group Public Company Limited,</i>

29
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:24,440
<i>Thailand's leading producer</i>
<i>of dramas and films.</i>

30
00:02:57,840 --> 00:03:01,160
Honestly, now that I've made it this far,
I'm so excited.

31
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,760
If you ask how ready I am,

32
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,240
I would give myself a 100 out of 10.

33
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:06,880
I'm more than ready.

34
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,960
I'm confident today will be fun.

35
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,720
- Hello, everyone.
- Hello.

36
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:15,240
Welcome, everyone,
to <i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4.</i>

37
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:19,360
The reality show highly-acclaimed
by its audience.

38
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:22,840
Over the past decade,
<i>The Face </i>has produced top-tier talent

39
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:27,440
for Thai entertainment and fashion,
launching hundreds of careers.

40
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:31,880
To celebrate <i>The Face</i>'s
10th season anniversary,

41
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:35,440
we are returning with the concept
"History in the Making."

42
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:38,960
Because the next The Face
will be made right here.

43
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:43,040
I'll prove that an Isan country boy
like me can go international.

44
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:45,800
Remember the name, Jodbush,
<i>The Face Men Season 4.</i>

45
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,880
Out of over 2,000 applicants worldwide,

46
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:52,520
you 44 are the ones who made the cut.

47
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,920
Congratulations to all of you.

48
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,720
Give yourselves a round of applause.

49
00:03:57,640 --> 00:04:00,880
<i>The final 44 out of 2,000.</i>
<i>I didn't even know there were 2,000.</i>

50
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:03,960
I somehow made it.
I'm nervous, but I'll do my absolute best.

51
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:06,680
- Okay, is everyone ready?
- Ready!

52
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,960
If you're all ready,

53
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:12,480
let's go meet the three mentors
for this season.

54
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:15,240
I only know two Thai celebrities.
Nadech and Yaya.

55
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,959
I heard a rumor
that one of the mentors is Mario.

56
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,240
Could it be him?

57
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:20,880
Our first mentor

58
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:26,160
is an actor who stars in series, films,
and even makes music.

59
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:30,640
On top of that, he works
behind the scenes as an executive.

60
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:32,640
Please give a big round of applause

61
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,320
for Mentor Mile Phakphum.

62
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,920
Hello, I'm Mile Phakphum.

63
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,040
<i>The godfather of the BL industry.</i>

64
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:46,000
A BL leading man with a world tour.
My god!

65
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:48,560
- Hello.
- Hello.

66
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,600
Are you nervous?

67
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,800
I'm a bit nervous,
but seeing everyone makes me feel…

68
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:55,120
Wow, there's so much great talent here.

69
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:58,440
Many of them caught my eye
right from the start.

70
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:02,120
Some clearly have potential,
but are still a bit shy.

71
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:06,000
We'll have to draw it out of them.
We still have some time.

72
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,000
Mr. Mafia.

73
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:11,120
I want a mafia mentor.

74
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:14,360
All right, let's move on
to our second mentor.

75
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,840
An actor who grew up

76
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:19,280
during a transitional era
in Thai entertainment.

77
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:22,360
He's a multi-talented actor.

78
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:25,760
Whether it's acting, dancing, or singing.

79
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,600
Or even hosting.

80
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:30,080
Please give a big round of applause

81
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,800
for Mentor Off Jumpol.

82
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:37,360
I'm Off, a legendary BL actor.

83
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,160
Not sure if I'm a legend,
I'll let others say that.

84
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,800
But I've been around for a decade.

85
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:44,920
This is it. I want to be with Off.
Making eye contact with him was like, wow.

86
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

87
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,320
This is my first time working
with Mentor Off.

88
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:53,360
But the look in his eyes
radiates pure mischief.

89
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,760
He is no joke.

90
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,640
But we still have one team left.

91
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:59,160
Our returning champion.

92
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:02,320
Someone with over a decade
of experience in the industry.

93
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,400
With masterpiece-level work.

94
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:09,480
Please give a round of applause
to welcome Mentor Pancake Khemanit.

95
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,960
I'm the only woman standing out there.
Looking around…

96
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:17,240
I'm surrounded by gentlemen.

97
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,920
Pancake looks so stunning, like an angel.

98
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,320
The most gorgeous woman.

99
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,840
Because I'm the only woman there.

100
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:29,640
I want to be on Pancake's team
because she has already made a champion.

101
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:33,520
If I had been here last season,
Bebe might not have won.

102
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:38,240
Of course, there's a slight difference
between the women's and men's seasons.

103
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:39,720
- A lot different.
- Right?

104
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:42,440
Totally different vibes.
Even the voices differ.

105
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:45,640
- I don't know about the ones next to me.
- We're starting already?

106
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:49,440
Coming out this strong, I have to ask
if Mentor Off is afraid of me.

107
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:53,480
Season 6 champion, so what?
This is a fresh start.

108
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,800
This is a new game.
Nothing to be afraid of.

109
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,880
But wait, everyone. Hold on.

110
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,240
This season, Mentor Pancake
isn't here alone.

111
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:05,680
Mentor Pancake is joined
by a highly talented actor

112
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:10,600
who has proven time and again
that he's the real deal.

113
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:15,000
Please give a round of applause
to welcome Mentor Ananda Everingham!

114
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,440
When Ananda came out, I was like this.

115
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,440
HONDA, 30 YEARS OLD

116
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:23,960
I'm Ananda. Just an actor.

117
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,120
- Hello.
- Hello.

118
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:31,120
Ananda is like
the Johnny Depp of Thailand.

119
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,280
So handsome.

120
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:34,840
The Mafia is here. The Papi is here.

121
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:37,400
And the other team
has Big Mommy and Big Daddy.

122
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:42,240
Daddy, train me.

123
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:44,440
- Hey, Mile, Off.
- Yes?

124
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:47,440
- You two had better just forfeit.
- Hey, wait. No way.

125
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,120
The show hasn't even started.

126
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:52,480
I'm not scared. If I were,
I wouldn't have accepted this job.

127
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,920
Isn't it a bit unfair?
There are two of them.

128
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,280
Don't be scared.
The game hasn't even started.

129
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,840
So fierce.

130
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,040
I'm in the middle.

131
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,440
Two is better than one.

132
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:04,240
I came alone,
so I feel like it's a bit unfair.

133
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,480
They were probably intimidated by Pancake.

134
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:10,160
Combined, we have almost
50 years of experience.

135
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,800
Half a century, man.

136
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:14,120
I just feel like we're at a disadvantage.

137
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:17,040
Next round,
let me have two mentors as well.

138
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,560
Oh, up to you.

139
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:20,960
Up to you. Go ahead.

140
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:23,840
I want someone unique

141
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:25,400
but natural.

142
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:31,320
I want the mentors to give me a chance,
so I can show what I've got.

143
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:34,840
It comes down to chemistry
and whether we click.

144
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:36,320
Whether we can get along.

145
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,720
I want someone positive and determined.

146
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:41,000
Someone who tries hard and fights for it.

147
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:45,080
As for talent and looks,
I believe everyone already has that.

148
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:48,600
What I really want to see today
is what they call "charisma."

149
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,360
Some people naturally have it.

150
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:54,080
If they can show that
throughout the entire competition,

151
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:56,200
I would love to see if that happens.

152
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:59,240
I think we're still looking for
diversity to emerge.

153
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,280
People with different talents.

154
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:05,960
Someone who is ready to be anything.
That's the person I'm looking for.

155
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,720
I would be happy on any team.

156
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:11,440
But I would be especially happy
to be on Ananda's team.

157
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:14,400
The surprises on our show don't end there.

158
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:18,840
Because this season, we have someone

159
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:22,000
who dictates the direction
of the Thai entertainment industry.

160
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:26,080
Moreover,
he has international working standards.

161
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:30,760
And today, he joins us
as a special Master Mentor

162
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:34,560
who will oversee
some of the rules on this show.

163
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:39,240
Please give a round of applause to welcome
Adam, M.R. Chalermchatri Yukol!

164
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:47,760
Such a big surprise
because Adam has so much work experience.

165
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:50,080
This year, I'm not going to stir the pot.

166
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,240
I'll keep it raw.

167
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:56,920
That raw, unscripted energy is
what I can bring to <i>The Face Men Season 4</i>.

168
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,520
I think it will be fun.

169
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,600
Let's see if he's here to help us,

170
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,760
get in our way, or what his next move is.

171
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:15,080
Welcome back to the auditions
we're all familiar with.

172
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,480
And this is the Face Shot round.

173
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:24,040
In this round,
contestants must walk out barefaced

174
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,160
and take a three-person group shot

175
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,920
under the concept "The Face Gangster."

176
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:32,000
For contestants to advance,

177
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:36,000
they must receive votes
from at least two of our mentors,

178
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:38,680
or be chosen by the Master Mentor.

179
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:41,120
Only those who pass this round

180
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:44,360
will move on with us
to the next audition phase.

181
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:47,760
I think that a unique, handsome person…

182
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:50,000
Someone who's completely natural…

183
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:53,160
I also want them to have
their own ideas at work.

184
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,960
The first group,
step out when you're ready.

185
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:02,240
Ale, Leo, Marilyn.

186
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:06,200
They came in with so much energy.
A great opening trio.

187
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:09,600
Ready.

188
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:11,600
- A group photo?
- Yes.

189
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,240
True. He gives off a Superman vibe.

190
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,640
He looks better in person.

191
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,840
Interesting.

192
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,520
How is Tiger?

193
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,840
They're so cute.

194
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,680
Please root for me on <i>The Face</i>.

195
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,320
Marilyn looks the most natural.

196
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:25,120
But we have to compare him
to the next 41 men.

197
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:28,280
If the Mentors want Marilyn
in the next round,

198
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,600
- Yes.
- …raise your hand.

199
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,720
Okay. And Leo.

200
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,800
And lastly, Ale.

201
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,880
Please tell Leo to breathe.

202
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:48,560
Yes, he just needs to relax.

203
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,880
Everyone did well.
Maybe because they're first.

204
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:54,360
We just haven't seen anyone
who really stands out yet.

205
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,960
There's no standard to compare them to.

206
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:59,920
Next three up, Pom, Manyoo, and Nonh.

207
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,480
Honestly, he looks way better in person.

208
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:03,680
Yes.

209
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:04,880
Good, very good.

210
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:08,440
Their take on the brief was okay.
The photo looks average.

211
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:10,640
- Excuse me.
- Do you need your glasses?

212
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,440
Never seen someone in glasses?

213
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,360
I get it. I'm not judging.

214
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,520
In a decade or so, I might be the same.

215
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,520
Can I come closer for a look?

216
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,880
Of course, go ahead.

217
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:26,400
I think I need an eye exam.

218
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,240
I have astigmatism.

219
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:30,160
It comes with age.

220
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,480
- So?
- That's strange.

221
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:32,800
- What's his name?
- Manyoo.

222
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:36,960
I don't know why,
but he looks nothing like his photo.

223
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,520
There's something about him.

224
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:41,680
Take off your jacket and strike a pose.
Three, two, one, pose.

225
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:44,560
See? He looks different
with a straight face.

226
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:46,360
Have you done this before?

227
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:48,880
I've done a bit of modeling.

228
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,880
What do you actually want to do?

229
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:53,240
Honestly, I want to be an actor.

230
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:56,960
Because I feel like being on TV

231
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:59,400
lets people around the world see you.

232
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:00,760
Everyone always says

233
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:04,520
they want <i>The Face </i>to be
their stepping stone to the spotlight.

234
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:07,720
This isn't just a stepping stone.
And it's not that easy.

235
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:10,120
Pom, what's your experience?

236
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:13,680
Modeling, photoshoots, and male pageants.

237
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,080
I see.

238
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,320
Why did you join the show?

239
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:22,000
I want to become a better model
and learn from the Mentors.

240
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,560
And from my fellow contestants.

241
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:26,480
If I had to pick one, I would choose Pom.

242
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:29,760
He's very humble.
His answers were quite interesting.

243
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:32,160
Okay. I think the Mentors
are ready to vote.

244
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,240
Nonh.

245
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,240
I say pass.

246
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,360
Pass.

247
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,520
Manyoo.

248
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,960
It's a no from me.

249
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,880
That was close.

250
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,000
Pass.

251
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:45,480
It's all up to Mentor Mile now.

252
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,440
I think he has potential
if he works at it.

253
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,560
Pass.

254
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,560
And our final guy, Pom.

255
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:56,680
- It's a no for Pom.
- That's a no.

256
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:57,640
Mentor Pancake?

257
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,120
It's a no.

258
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:02,560
I honestly don't get
why they didn't pass Pom.

259
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:06,080
I was so sure
he was going to end up on my team.

260
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,520
I don't get it. Really.

261
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:10,040
That means… Pom, you are not The Face.

262
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:12,520
Am I disappointed? A little bit.

263
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,720
If I get the chance,
I'd love to come back.

264
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,840
I'd really like to give it another shot.

265
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:19,040
Next group, please come in.

266
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,160
I remember him.

267
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:22,760
When he was in line,
he looked interesting.

268
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,720
- They have the same style.
- True.

269
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:28,480
We just hit our poses right away
because we prepared a bit beforehand.

270
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:31,720
If I saw this trio,
I wouldn't approach them.

271
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,520
What do the left and right hands mean?

272
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,280
I wanted to show we're a gang
and I'm holding my friends back.

273
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:39,560
- This is holding your friends back?
- Like "don't go."

274
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:42,960
At first, I thought
these hands meant, "They're mine."

275
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:46,760
I got it wrong, right?
It's not wrong. It's fine.

276
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,080
Gangsters can have

277
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:50,800
- that kind of dynamic too.
- Of course, they can.

278
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,520
I like this trio the best.

279
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:55,920
They nailed the brief.
The photo stood out most.

280
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,440
Is Jodbush your real name?

281
00:15:57,520 --> 00:16:01,360
Yes, it is. But some people call me
Bak Jod. It's up to them.

282
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:04,840
- Sometimes people call me Bak Joi.
- Bak Joi? Our names are similar.

283
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:06,760
Our names both start with J.

284
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,880
- I like your vibe.
- Thank you so much.

285
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:09,800
I say pass.

286
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:11,040
Oh, just like that?

287
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:13,280
- So?
- I'm okay with that. Really.

288
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:15,360
- You pass. You're through.
- Thank you.

289
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:17,880
- You pass.
- Thank you, Mile. Thank you, everyone.

290
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,960
I feel good. Everyone seems so friendly.

291
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:23,360
I like it.
Good energy helps me perform well.

292
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,320
Let's move on to Donut.

293
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:28,320
Are you a shy person?

294
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,760
Fundamentally, a little bit.

295
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,000
Why did you join this show?

296
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:34,120
Because I want to prove myself.
I want to learn new things.

297
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:37,720
I want to gain experiences
that I can really build upon.

298
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,440
- What do you do for a living?
- I'm a vendor.

299
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:42,480
I sell noodles and Isan sausages.

300
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:45,200
Hello, I'm Donut. I'm 25 years old.

301
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:48,840
Currently, I own
Sripatum Thai BBQ pork skewers.

302
00:16:48,920 --> 00:16:51,080
I also own Por Patum Boat Noodles.

303
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:54,960
My mom has run the noodle shop
for about 30 years.

304
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,800
We started as a small roadside stall.

305
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:58,240
I do almost everything.

306
00:16:58,320 --> 00:17:02,800
After I graduated, my mom handed
the noodle shop over to me to run.

307
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,960
It's not famous, but it's delicious.
Maybe soon.

308
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:07,880
BOAT NOODLES

309
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:13,440
I love food, and I love fashion.
I like modeling and photography.

310
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,359
I've known about <i>The Face</i>
since I was a kid.

311
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:18,560
I saw applications were open,
so I wanted to prove myself.

312
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:21,640
Please support
and cheer for me on the show.

313
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:24,800
- Could you describe your tattoos?
- The bottom one is a font.

314
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:27,000
The dragon represents my birth year.

315
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:28,760
Oh, you pass.

316
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:30,640
- Just like that?
- I'm Year of the Dragon too.

317
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,080
- Is that allowed?
- Just like that?

318
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,480
You can't do that, right?

319
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,120
I think she likes my uniqueness.

320
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,480
Yes, I'm really impressed.

321
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:38,680
How about this?

322
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:41,280
I want to see more tattoos.
I think Mentor Pancake does too.

323
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:42,960
Can you show your tattoos to her?

324
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,400
I didn't even ask.

325
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,800
Could you please take off your shirt?

326
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,720
Oh, the top.

327
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:52,680
When Donut had to take off his shirt,
he did it, but he was really awkward.

328
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:56,400
It shows he lacks confidence.
He has his guard up.

329
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,880
That might be an issue
for short-term projects.

330
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:01,600
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

331
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:02,640
I say pass.

332
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:06,280
Donut truly represents
what it means to be a fighter.

333
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:08,920
Like, taking today off
means he loses income.

334
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,960
Why is he here? To follow his dream.

335
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:12,520
I really want him to succeed.

336
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:16,480
Peem, you've done a lot of things.
You're a TV series lead too.

337
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:18,560
- Which TV series did you act in?
- <i>Kla Talay</i>.

338
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:23,360
I have studied acting,
and now I'm making my own music too.

339
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:26,160
- What genre of music?
- It's R&B.

340
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:29,520
- Let's hear you sing an R&B song.
- I can actually sing my own song.

341
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:30,960
Give it a try.

342
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:35,520
<i>The scent of your perfume drifting by</i>

343
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:39,640
<i>Just let it show, no need to be shy</i>

344
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:44,840
<i>Oh, I want you, you, you</i>

345
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,760
Okay, I say pass.

346
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:47,840
- Pass.
- Pass.

347
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:50,280
- I love his natural vibe.
- Thank you so much.

348
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,000
Those who sing have that artistic flair.

349
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:54,360
If we give him the space
to express himself…

350
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:57,920
I think there's something there
we might not have seen yet.

351
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,400
Whether we find it is another story.

352
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,360
You did it!

353
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:06,240
The way to catch their eye
is how you present yourself.

354
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:09,600
Next group, Jimmy, Luca, and Aagatung.

355
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:12,760
- Come on.
- This is Aagatung.

356
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:14,160
He's a <i>Mor Lam </i>singer.

357
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:18,000
I'm Aagatung,
I'm from Silapinputhai Mor Lam troupe.

358
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,000
I'm a young leading man.

359
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,400
A <i>Mor Lam </i>singer must be able to sing.

360
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,720
Singing, dancing, and rhythm
must be on point.

361
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:29,000
<i>Mentors, which mentor wants to choose me?</i>

362
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:36,080
<i>If any mentor wants to have fun</i>
<i>And dance, choose Aagatung</i>

363
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:37,920
Do you have a concept?

364
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,880
Yes, kind of a retro gangster.

365
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,360
Hey, he can speak Thai.

366
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:43,840
Yes.

367
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:45,280
Jimmy, where are you from?

368
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:47,280
I'm half-Thai, half-French.

369
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:49,000
- Really?
- I speak Southern Thai too.

370
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:51,320
- Southern Thai?
- He's speaking Southern Thai.

371
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,880
I speak Isan dialect too.

372
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:58,080
Jimmy seems to have a bright future.
I didn't expect him to be so charming.

373
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:59,320
Jimmy is perfect for Mile.

374
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:03,000
You're cool. You also make music.

375
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:03,920
Thank you.

376
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:07,160
But I might not bring out
his full potential like Mile can,

377
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,160
since Mile makes music.

378
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,520
Do you like making music?

379
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,120
Yes, I'm a beat maker.

380
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:15,120
He's actually a great fit for Mentor Mile.

381
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:19,080
For artists, dancing, and singing,
we have quite a few strong candidates.

382
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:22,160
What do you think, Mile? He's interesting.

383
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:25,640
I don't expect
my whole team to become artists.

384
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:26,880
This is <i>The Face Men.</i>

385
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:30,360
His singing skills
won't be of much use here.

386
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,360
I have to act friendly first.

387
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:36,360
Then I show my true colors.

388
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:40,400
It seems all three mentors
really like Jimmy.

389
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:42,280
But I see it differently.

390
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:49,240
I can tell all three are professionals,
but it's the same old routine.

391
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,160
They can do much better.

392
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:56,280
I expect 100 or 120 percent.

393
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:58,240
The Master Mentor disagrees.

394
00:20:58,320 --> 00:21:00,760
That's fine.
He only spent two days with them.

395
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:04,520
Makes sense. I don't hold it against him.

396
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,520
Luca, do you speak Thai?

397
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:07,840
Oh, just a little.

398
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:14,200
Six years. That's all you know?
Are you crazy?

399
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,360
- I should speak better Thai. I know.
- Yeah.

400
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,280
He's good-looking.

401
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,240
Try to speak more Thai.

402
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:22,840
- Yes, I understand.
- All right.

403
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:33,000
He looks so handsome with his hair back.

404
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:35,680
Luca, you would go so far
if you spoke Thai.

405
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,880
You must speak the language
to be an actor.

406
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:39,960
Language aside, I want to see him walk.

407
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:41,320
- Pass.
- Pass.

408
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,640
I want to see him walk.

409
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:45,760
All right, the other two. Jimmy.

410
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,800
- I want to see him walk too.
- Pass.

411
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:50,040
Aagatung?

412
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:51,960
- I want to see him walk.
- Same.

413
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:55,760
I have to disagree with you all. I say no.

414
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:57,600
I say no.

415
00:21:57,680 --> 00:22:00,400
My job is to screen them, so I will.

416
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,560
Sorry.

417
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:04,000
Let him walk, and I'll decide.

418
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,880
Oh, okay.

419
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:09,560
The Master Mentor passed him
just like that?

420
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,680
Why am I even here?

421
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:13,160
He could just do this alone without me.

422
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:15,360
I'm just confused. I don't get it.

423
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:18,840
Lucky you. You get to do the walk.

424
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:21,640
- That's bad. Everyone gets to walk.
- Aren't we eliminating anyone?

425
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:25,040
I genuinely want to know
what the Master Mentor sees in him.

426
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:27,720
Next group. PP, Tino, and Toosafe.

427
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,440
The guy in the back.

428
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:31,760
We have to watch PP too.

429
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:34,040
Three, two, one.

430
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:37,840
I'll be honest. The photo isn't great.

431
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:41,280
The shot makes it look like
we don't even know each other.

432
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:43,640
We're all doing our own thing.

433
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:44,880
PP, explain the concept.

434
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:49,320
We're a trio of pretty men in black who…

435
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:50,520
are cute.

436
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,280
Why are you looking at them?

437
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:54,360
- Yes?
- He's nervous and lacks confidence.

438
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:55,440
I'm nervous.

439
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:58,040
I was so stiff up there.
I didn't know what to do.

440
00:22:58,120 --> 00:23:00,600
The challenge was a photoshoot,
and the photo…

441
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,360
It's probably because…

442
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:05,680
There were so many cameras
and I was nervous.

443
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:10,520
I just hope the mentors give us
a chance to move to the next round.

444
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:12,480
We'll prove ourselves to everyone.

445
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:17,120
I think we just didn't prepare enough
for this specific challenge.

446
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:21,200
Toosafe, do you have anything to say
to get to know you better?

447
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,760
I've been a huge fan
of <i>The Face </i>for a while.

448
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:26,840
I didn't think
I was the show's type at all.

449
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:29,280
But from watching various fashion shows,

450
00:23:29,360 --> 00:23:30,520
I've seen LGBTQ+ models

451
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:34,520
and those who don't fit
traditional beauty standards.

452
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:38,240
The industry is more inclusive now.
It made me feel like I could be there.

453
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,200
I want to see Toosafe walk.

454
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,960
I'm sorry to the other two.

455
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:45,440
- But…
- Here we go again.

456
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:47,280
I'm truly sorry.

457
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:50,280
Toosafe, the problem
is your choice of words is terrible.

458
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:53,440
You were sitting right by the runway.

459
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:55,200
Saying that
if they can do it, you can too.

460
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:57,680
It implies that
if anyone can walk a runway,

461
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:01,360
be in a boy band or be Lisa from Blackpink
or be absolutely anything, then so can I.

462
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,840
That's a strange mindset.

463
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:06,360
They're professionals
who worked their whole lives.

464
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:10,360
They possess certain skills
honed through their careers.

465
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:13,240
I felt I genuinely wanted to do
what I pitched.

466
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:15,920
But maybe it comes down
to my interpretation.

467
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,360
That's how I understood it.

468
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:18,960
I'd like you to head back for now.

469
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:20,960
If you want to try again,
our doors are open.

470
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:23,400
We're always ready.

471
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:26,200
Ready for anyone, regardless of age.
We never discriminate.

472
00:24:26,280 --> 00:24:29,840
I just cannot accept it.
I don't want to accept it.

473
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:33,440
Tino, you've modeled before.
I expected more from you.

474
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,760
I needed you to walk in here
with more confidence.

475
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:41,520
With higher standards,
we see with a different lens.

476
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:45,280
Honestly, I disagree a bit,
because I feel I'm determined enough.

477
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,520
I came here today to get first place.

478
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:50,840
They just didn't see my potential
or perspective, and that's fine.

479
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:53,440
That's it. None of the three passed.

480
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:55,200
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

481
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:57,560
The Master Mentor eliminated all of them.

482
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:00,640
It's a shame. It feels like…

483
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,320
Let's move on to the next group.

484
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,920
Three, Arm, and Dan.

485
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:13,160
I'm Police Lance Corporal Three Uamkham.

486
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:17,320
I want everyone
to not be afraid of the police.

487
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:23,640
I'd love everyone to keep an open mind.
Let me show everyone my playful side.

488
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,960
Why did I become a cop?

489
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:27,640
My dad is a cop.

490
00:25:27,720 --> 00:25:29,960
My uncle is a cop. My grandpa is a cop.

491
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:32,640
So, I became one too.

492
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:37,120
I believe being a police officer
and a model can go hand in hand.

493
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,960
Please root for this cop too.

494
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,160
If you cheat on this show,

495
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:45,720
I'll actually arrest you. You're busted.

496
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:49,080
Take your photos now. One shot only.

497
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:51,560
What's the title of this series?

498
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:53,560
It's a new interpretation.

499
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,800
It's about gangsters,

500
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:58,640
but with a romantic angle
involved as well.

501
00:25:58,720 --> 00:26:01,920
I like his idea.
He delivered a very clear presentation.

502
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:05,200
His strength is that he had a backstory
before the shoot.

503
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:07,080
When he explained it, it made sense.

504
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:08,720
What will <i>The Face </i>give you?

505
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:12,080
It will let the whole world,

506
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:14,280
or the whole country,

507
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:17,960
see how much
I can achieve in this industry.

508
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:21,400
I might be starting out
with less experience than others,

509
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:24,040
but I'm confident
I'm ready to learn and improve.

510
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:25,200
I love what he said.

511
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:27,920
Beginning, middle, and end.
He had it all mapped out.

512
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,320
Because he's a doctor.

513
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,720
He's an academic man.

514
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:32,800
Pass.

515
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:35,040
- Wow, just like that?
- I'll give it to him.

516
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:38,600
I'm still not entirely sure
if he fits <i>The Face</i>'s standards.

517
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:42,280
There's a high chance
he won't be able to keep up.

518
00:26:44,280 --> 00:26:46,480
Pass. I give you a pass.

519
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:47,680
Thank you.

520
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:50,440
I'd love to work
with Mentor Off or Mentor Mile.

521
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,520
Honestly, whoever picks me at this point,

522
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:54,720
I'll do my best to help the team win.

523
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:57,560
Have you been in the industry before?
It feels like you have.

524
00:26:57,640 --> 00:26:59,200
I've shot some commercials.

525
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:01,560
You have quite a sensitive family story.

526
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:02,880
Could you elaborate?

527
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:07,240
I love my family more than anything.
I mean…

528
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:10,560
I…

529
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:14,560
My priority isn't myself.
I choose my family first.

530
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:19,440
I don't know if that's a strength
or a weakness, but…

531
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:21,840
That's the choice I made.

532
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:24,080
I get very emotional
when it comes to family too.

533
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,120
I like him.

534
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:27,160
It's definitely a strength.

535
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,440
Gratitude will never drag you down.

536
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:33,120
- You have the right mindset.
- I like him. I think he's natural.

537
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:34,160
Pass.

538
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:36,000
As soon as Dan feels it, he shows it.

539
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:39,360
If he could channel those core emotions,

540
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:43,000
he could become
an incredibly talented actor.

541
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:45,680
- And what about Three?
- We want to see him walk.

542
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:48,280
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

543
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:49,280
Thank you.

544
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:53,400
I don't feel entirely great about it
because there's still another round.

545
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:57,480
Next group. Lincoln, Jacob, and Bonus.

546
00:27:57,560 --> 00:27:59,960
Come on in.

547
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:04,480
Bonus stands out from the others.

548
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:05,680
What's the concept?

549
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,720
Gangsters. A hundred percent swag.

550
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:10,600
Making angry faces, like bad boys.

551
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:13,080
- Wait, you speak Thai?
- I do.

552
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,920
Hey, that's not bad.

553
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,280
Wait, are you Thai or not?

554
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:19,360
I'm not Thai. I'm from Germany,
but my parents are Vietnamese.

555
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,880
- Vietnamese.
- Oh, Vietnamese.

556
00:28:20,960 --> 00:28:22,560
How did you end up in Thailand?

557
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:26,760
I really wanted to live here
because Thailand already feels like home.

558
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:28,560
Smart answer.

559
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:32,480
He was a bit surprised I could speak Thai.

560
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:35,360
Bonus, any previous experience
in this industry?

561
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:38,200
- No. This is my first.
- Really? What made you join the show?

562
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:41,160
- A friend invited me.
- You came with a friend.

563
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:43,160
- Yes.
- Now, you're in the competition.

564
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:46,040
- What's your goal now?
- I'll give it my all. I love it.

565
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:48,760
I love this feeling.
The excitement, then the pride.

566
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:51,760
You've never modeled
or walked a runway before. You…

567
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:52,800
Just on TikToks.

568
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:56,320
The photo isn't perfect
and so was the brief.

569
00:28:56,400 --> 00:29:00,800
But he convinced us
why we should pick him.

570
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:02,840
I'm excited. Ananda is so handsome. Sorry.

571
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:03,920
Pass! You're through.

572
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:06,120
- Hey! Hold on a second.
- Hey!

573
00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:08,760
I like him.
I want someone like this on my team.

574
00:29:08,840 --> 00:29:10,280
But he likes Ananda.

575
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:11,800
Oh, Mile…

576
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:15,880
I want him, so I just say it straight.
No need to complicate things.

577
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:19,760
No, but I think he's very natural.
He doesn't look pressured at all.

578
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:23,080
- He's pushing you to be on his team.
- Hey, too late for that.

579
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:27,960
I'm taking my time so I don't miss out.
He's more persuasive.

580
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:29,120
I'm nervous.

581
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,240
But I'm sincere.

582
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:31,680
I think Mile is interested.

583
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:33,040
Because of his gentleness.

584
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:36,760
There's something deeper.
I think he's more strategic than Off.

585
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:39,680
The right choice
isn't always the one you like.

586
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:41,240
So choose your partner wisely.

587
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:43,200
I don't love you anymore. I'll hit you.

588
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,480
I'm good. You all pass.

589
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:47,120
- You all pass.
- Everyone passes.

590
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:50,280
I'll be fine with Mile or Ananda.
But it's up to them.

591
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:51,280
I'm open.

592
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:54,320
- See? Now you let him pass.
- He was breaking the ice earlier.

593
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,000
It was really awkward before.

594
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:59,320
I think I'll just keep being myself
throughout the whole show.

595
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:02,320
If they like me, great.
If not, then bye-bye.

596
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:06,320
Mentors, ready for the next group?

597
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:08,840
- Ready.
- All right, bring in the next group.

598
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,760
- Is this group entirely LGBTQ+?
- Yes.

599
00:30:12,840 --> 00:30:14,040
Hello, my name is Honda.

600
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:16,440
I'm currently a freelance dancer.

601
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:24,640
I'm so happy when I dance.
I feel like I'm releasing my inner energy.

602
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:26,960
And I feel that
when I'm up there on stage,

603
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:29,120
my job is to entertain the audience.

604
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:31,560
I was a dance sport athlete
when I was younger.

605
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,480
I had the chance
to compete at the highest level,

606
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:35,400
the University Games of Thailand.

607
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:38,120
I won four medals.

608
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:41,840
I watched the previous seasons,
and the newbies tend to freeze up on set.

609
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:44,480
So I want to tell
the younger contestants on the show,

610
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:46,360
you'd better prepare yourselves.

611
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:48,120
Be careful when we meet on set…

612
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:50,080
or you might freeze up.

613
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:54,600
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight, and one.

614
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:57,840
What's the concept?

615
00:30:57,920 --> 00:31:01,440
We wanted to look like a gangster crew

616
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:03,600
hanging out in front of a club.

617
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:09,080
We put our all into it
and planned it very carefully.

618
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:11,680
For this photoshoot round,
we only get one shot.

619
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:14,400
Earlier,
I saw them counting during the shoot.

620
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:16,200
They were counting the beat.

621
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:17,280
What was that about?

622
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:19,680
During rehearsal,
we wanted to create a moment

623
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:21,880
where on "and one",
everyone gives it their all.

624
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:27,280
I want to know why you're so determined
to go to Hong Kong Disneyland.

625
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:28,640
I've been taking dance classes
since I was a kid.

626
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:30,480
I would dance in front of the mirror

627
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,240
whenever I heard
the royal news theme song.

628
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:36,040
So I just knew I was going to be
a dancer when I grew up.

629
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:39,200
My dream in this industry is
to win the NineEntertain Awards.

630
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:40,800
Or maybe Nataraja or Suphannahong Awards.

631
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:42,520
- Oh, wow.
- Oh, wow.

632
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,200
Man, I don't want to brag.

633
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:46,280
Wait, have you won all of them?

634
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,720
Hey, I can't brag about these things.

635
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:50,240
The third floor of my house
is full of awards.

636
00:31:50,320 --> 00:31:54,800
But before the Nataraja or Suphannahong,
you have to get through this show first.

637
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:57,360
Let's focus on that first, shall we?

638
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:00,480
Fifa, why do you look so unsure?

639
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:01,720
I'm just nervous.

640
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:04,040
You're not boxed into one style, right?

641
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:09,280
I've seen some people walk
as both male and female models.

642
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:11,280
Whether I'm given
women's or men's clothes,

643
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:13,480
I'll do my absolute best on the runway.

644
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:15,720
This group is already very special.

645
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:18,200
They have their own talents
and can do so many things.

646
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:21,240
If they just have
the courage to let it out.

647
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:24,200
Yes, competing on <i>The Face Men</i>
doesn't pressure me at all.

648
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,600
I used to be a cis man.

649
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:28,640
My dad is also a cis man.
What could scare me?

650
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:31,280
Plus, I'm into men now anyway.

651
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:32,400
That's fabulous.

652
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:35,680
Whenever I work as a model,

653
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:37,080
I can do both roles.

654
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:40,080
Whether portraying a woman or a man,
I'll do my best.

655
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:41,120
I like them.

656
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:43,720
- All of them.
- I like the energy.

657
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:45,960
I like the vibe of these three.

658
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,360
Bring all three in. You all pass.

659
00:32:49,320 --> 00:32:50,720
I like all of them.

660
00:32:50,800 --> 00:32:53,240
They're a perfect combination.

661
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:56,000
Gems, Man, and Rcha.

662
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:58,040
They're showing off their muscles.

663
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:00,600
Their bodies are amazing.

664
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:04,160
Built like a tank.
Packed with high-quality protein.

665
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,680
I can't even look.

666
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:08,400
Are they showing off too much?

667
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:11,040
You take your shirt off too.

668
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:13,800
There has to be a reason to show off.
What is it?

669
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:16,040
The concept is that we're the locals here.

670
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:18,320
We're here to reclaim our territory.

671
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:19,680
But the poses are okay.

672
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:22,440
Rcha, I just met your friend, Bonus.

673
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:24,080
Why did you drag him along?

674
00:33:24,160 --> 00:33:25,400
He has the right look.

675
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:29,640
I want to support my friend.
He's super cool, edgy, and smart.

676
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:32,160
Gems has actually done quite a bit.

677
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:34,240
Not a lot. Just some guest appearances.

678
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:37,240
Mostly playing the villain.

679
00:33:37,320 --> 00:33:39,440
Or playing a thief, things like that.

680
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:42,640
Why do you think we will choose you?

681
00:33:42,720 --> 00:33:46,160
I feel like the show would be
pretty bland without me.

682
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:50,680
I can feel it. There's an awkwardness
I can't quite explain.

683
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:52,960
It feels like a negative attitude.

684
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:54,800
It just makes me cringe.

685
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:56,120
What do you say, Off?

686
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,680
I want to see Man walk.

687
00:33:58,280 --> 00:34:00,400
I want Rcha to go in and meet Bonus.

688
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:03,560
I don't think Gems is
the right fit for me.

689
00:34:04,920 --> 00:34:08,760
Okay, I want to see him walk alongside
his friend. I want to see Rcha.

690
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:13,400
Man, I like your uniqueness.
I like the mustache too.

691
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:14,679
I want to see Man walk.

692
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:17,760
I'll try my best in every round.

693
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:20,840
I think it might get us
to the final round.

694
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:25,480
I'm here today because I want something
truly unique and natural.

695
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,159
Sorry, Gems. Not today.

696
00:34:27,239 --> 00:34:30,239
- I accept that.
- It's far from natural.

697
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:33,280
He might have rehearsed it,
but that's how I really feel.

698
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:35,199
First off, acting doesn't lie.

699
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,960
Your muscles are tense.

700
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:42,760
What you're saying and what you're
expressing physically don't match.

701
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:44,480
My muscles are tense?

702
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:49,000
I didn't realize that.
I was just trying to relax.

703
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:51,880
And acting like this is the dark arts.

704
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:54,000
I believe everyone sees it.

705
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:55,800
From here, the Mentors can see everything.

706
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:57,080
Go work on it first.

707
00:34:57,160 --> 00:35:00,280
Our doors are always open.
We're not going anywhere.

708
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:02,360
Honestly, you can't fake acting.

709
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:06,400
This is just you processing thoughts
and putting on an act.

710
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:10,880
I guess I understand that I might not be
a blank slate like the others.

711
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:13,480
Sorry, Gems. You're not The Face.

712
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:14,520
Thank you.

713
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:17,200
Maybe my actions were wrong.
I'm not the right fit.

714
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:19,400
Maybe it's just not the place for me.

715
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:21,440
Go change your mindset first.

716
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:24,360
Next group. Sky, Che, and Fox.

717
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:26,800
Why is no one doing it like…

718
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:28,320
Yes.

719
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:32,120
The theme is gangster,
and there are many types of gangsters.

720
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:34,880
You can definitely think outside the box.

721
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:37,560
Our character is a high-class mafia.

722
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:40,960
But we're focusing on
the inner energy from all three of us.

723
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:42,800
It feels like we've seen this before.

724
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:44,360
Yes, very average.

725
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:46,200
It's a pity they didn't add more depth.

726
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:50,160
Take a risk,
try something else to present.

727
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:51,960
- Fox.
- Can you push your hair up?

728
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:55,760
I actually liked him
since I saw his picture.

729
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:58,000
He looked better with his hair swept back.

730
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:59,440
- Are you half-Thai?
- Yes.

731
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:01,200
- Half what?
- Thai-Australian.

732
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:03,920
Actually, I was born in Surin.

733
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:06,600
When I was in seventh or eighth grade,

734
00:36:06,680 --> 00:36:09,960
I moved to live
with my parents in England.

735
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:13,200
He looks good when he speaks.

736
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:14,360
Right.

737
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:17,000
What about Che?
Can you compete with your friends?

738
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:19,640
Yes. Personally, I'm an actor.

739
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:21,360
I'm currently a flight attendant.

740
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:24,200
And what if you become a star?

741
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:26,360
My flight schedule is issued in advance.

742
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:29,880
I can just swap
my flight days for days off.

743
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:30,840
Really?

744
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:35,200
Suppose you have acting gigs
for 15 or 20 days.

745
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,800
- I can manage it.
- Can you?

746
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:37,960
Is that a good idea?

747
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:41,040
You need to be dedicated.
You have to pick one.

748
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:44,440
I feel like I can do both concurrently.

749
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:46,160
I believe in human potential.

750
00:36:46,240 --> 00:36:49,920
I get it, but if my teacher heard this,
you would be dead.

751
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:52,920
Things are easier today.
There are more opportunities.

752
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:56,840
But becoming a quality actor
is still tough.

753
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:59,720
It's not just about talent.
It takes dedication.

754
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:02,840
I truly believe we can do both.

755
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:07,360
But I've learned that the art of acting,
or the work we do,

756
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:09,880
requires time and practice.

757
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:12,040
It takes deep understanding,
not just effort.

758
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:13,880
I want you to think it over.

759
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:17,400
When the time comes,
it won't be as easy as you think.

760
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:19,960
I doubt your mindset
coming into this show.

761
00:37:20,040 --> 00:37:21,440
That mindset is wrong.

762
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:25,000
I'm only passing Fox.

763
00:37:25,080 --> 00:37:27,120
- Are you copying me?
- I had no idea.

764
00:37:27,200 --> 00:37:29,320
Same here. I'm passing Fox.

765
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,640
He almost failed because of his hair.

766
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:33,840
But his personality and looks are solid.

767
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:38,400
There's still a runway round
where I want him to prove himself.

768
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:40,760
Excuse me, may I interject?

769
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:43,760
Right now, you passed
just because you speak well.

770
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:47,760
I don't want the Mentors to use
these criteria for <i>The Face</i>.

771
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:49,520
That's not a good standard.

772
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:52,160
- Right.
- I want the Mentors to choose the best.

773
00:37:53,560 --> 00:37:59,200
I think, from one perspective,
if the audience wants more of him,

774
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:01,640
shouldn't we give them that chance?

775
00:38:01,720 --> 00:38:03,720
Can we persuade him?

776
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:07,080
It's fine. If his walk is bad,
we won't pick him.

777
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:08,000
Is that okay?

778
00:38:08,080 --> 00:38:11,840
The final decision
is up to Master Mentor Adam.

779
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:12,880
What do you say?

780
00:38:13,600 --> 00:38:15,000
Let's wait and see.

781
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:16,000
Okay, go.

782
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,400
Pass.

783
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,440
Thank you. Thank you so much.

784
00:38:19,520 --> 00:38:23,000
I made it through. I'm so happy
and really excited for the next round.

785
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:25,760
He also mentioned
he likes high-energy Mentors.

786
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:27,840
- But he lacks energy himself.
- Right.

787
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:29,160
Can we bring Fox back?

788
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:31,040
I'm having a heart attack now.

789
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:34,960
Everyone wants to see you walk,
but you wrote in your profile that

790
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,200
you like energetic Mentors.

791
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:38,360
But we need to see that energy
from you too.

792
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:40,240
Don't demand what you can't deliver.

793
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:42,800
- See you in the next round.
- She's really serious.

794
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:44,520
Her intensity is just…

795
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:46,400
terrifying.

796
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:47,840
Next group, please.

797
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:50,640
Yanis, Peakker, Ball.

798
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:51,960
They look so young.

799
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:54,480
This is probably the youngest group.

800
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,240
What do you think, Off?

801
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:59,000
It will be tough for them
to compete with the others.

802
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:02,040
I'm failing all of you.

803
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:04,560
You might not be a good fit here yet.

804
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:06,200
Let's meet again in two years.

805
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:09,360
Honestly, I agree with Off.

806
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,520
It's a no from me.

807
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:17,280
I feel a bit discouraged, but I…

808
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,480
Calm down. The Master Mentor is here.

809
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:22,720
I want to see you fight for another round.

810
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:26,680
I want to see Peakker in another round.
I want to see more.

811
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:29,400
But control yourself a bit.
You have too much energy.

812
00:39:29,480 --> 00:39:31,240
We'll see during the walk.

813
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:35,040
Whether what Adam sees
is what everyone else will see.

814
00:39:35,120 --> 00:39:37,040
Only Peakker advances.

815
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:38,960
As for Yanis and Ball,

816
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:40,920
I'm sorry. You're not The Face.

817
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:43,200
I might look young, but I know my limits.

818
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:46,000
That's about it. Thank you very much.

819
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:49,280
Next group, Nick, Driver, and Joseph.

820
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:51,520
This gang walked in
without greeting anyone.

821
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:53,920
Yes, I think basic manners are important.

822
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,880
I feel like there's nothing new here.

823
00:39:56,960 --> 00:40:00,560
Since all three of them are models,

824
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:02,760
they should have been more creative.

825
00:40:02,840 --> 00:40:05,200
I really don't see the gangster vibe.

826
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:08,640
The energy they gave off
didn't have that vibe at all.

827
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:11,080
We've already seen so much of this.

828
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:13,480
The Mentors might start feeling like…

829
00:40:13,560 --> 00:40:14,520
Time to choose.

830
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:16,840
Okay, what's your name?

831
00:40:16,920 --> 00:40:18,720
I'm Joseph. Joseph Dixon.

832
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:20,360
Only Joseph passes.

833
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:21,880
- Me too.
- Yes.

834
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:24,160
You're models, but you didn't use it
to your advantage.

835
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:25,440
So…

836
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:26,680
go home.

837
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:30,600
Sorry if we seem unenthusiastic,
but we cannot be here all night.

838
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:33,480
Come on, let's go.

839
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:35,960
All right, next group, please.

840
00:40:36,040 --> 00:40:39,360
I'm 100% confident. I have the confidence.
I'm a real gangster.

841
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:41,160
- This one is Wigrom.
- Hello.

842
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:44,160
Wow, look at that.
I don't like this at all.

843
00:40:44,240 --> 00:40:46,040
One, two…

844
00:40:48,120 --> 00:40:50,160
- The middle guy looks cool.
- I like him.

845
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:51,560
He's very photogenic.

846
00:40:51,640 --> 00:40:53,720
- Sorry, what's your name?
- Travis.

847
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:55,640
- I'll just call you Mew.
- Oh, Mew.

848
00:40:55,720 --> 00:40:57,080
- You can call me Mew.
- That's different.

849
00:40:57,160 --> 00:40:58,760
My nickname is Bak Joi too.

850
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:02,760
Mew stood out the most.

851
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:06,600
He's a perfect fit for this show,
and a perfect fit for my team.

852
00:41:06,680 --> 00:41:07,520
I liked him the best.

853
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:10,360
- And next up… what's your name again?
- I'm Wigrom.

854
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:13,880
Wigrom, I just want to know one thing.
Why did you walk in like that?

855
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:15,640
To give off a gangster vibe.

856
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:18,840
I wanted to show you right away
that I'm a gangster.

857
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:20,840
You really thought it through?

858
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:23,760
- Believe me, if we didn't ask…
- If we didn't, you'd be gone.

859
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:25,240
You didn't connect with us at all, bro.

860
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:28,160
Oops, excuse me.
You didn't connect with us.

861
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:31,480
I was a bit hesitant about Wigrom.

862
00:41:31,560 --> 00:41:34,920
Because I felt like
he looked super confident.

863
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:37,480
But standing right there, he seemed…

864
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:39,320
completely insecure.

865
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:41,000
What are you normally like?

866
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:44,360
Handsome. A pianist. A musician.

867
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:46,960
<i>I'm an influencer.</i>

868
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:49,880
<i>The owner of a famous TikTok channel</i>
<i>called Raw Milk King.</i>

869
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:52,120
I'm Patchubun Panjamapirom.
My nickname is Wigrom.

870
00:41:52,720 --> 00:41:56,320
<i>I once saw a face-changing mask show</i>
<i>at a provincial Chinese opera.</i>

871
00:41:56,400 --> 00:41:58,680
<i>I told my mom I wanted to be like them.</i>

872
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,400
<i>My parents totally supported me.</i>

873
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:06,880
<i>As for my special talents, I'm a pianist.</i>
<i>A musician and a piano composer.</i>

874
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:08,320
<i>I can play the xylophone.</i>

875
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:09,240
<i>I'm also a magician.</i>

876
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:13,040
<i>And my own personal nutritionist.</i>

877
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:17,520
<i>I study nutrition,</i>
<i>focusing on natural foods.</i>

878
00:42:17,600 --> 00:42:19,800
<i>I believe it makes me even more handsome.</i>

879
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:23,360
Even though I'm a catch,
a handsome guy like me chooses <i>The Face</i>.

880
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:26,800
By joining <i>The Face</i>,
what do you actually want to be?

881
00:42:26,880 --> 00:42:28,760
I want to be The Face.

882
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:32,400
But being on <i>The Face</i>
means facing lots of different challenges.

883
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:35,120
- Do you think you can handle that?
- I can. Absolutely.

884
00:42:35,200 --> 00:42:36,960
I was impressed by Mentor Pancake.

885
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:40,200
I was a little thrilled.
It definitely boosted my confidence.

886
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:41,280
PP.

887
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:42,800
Tell us about yourself.

888
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:45,480
I'm currently a sophomore
studying here in Thailand.

889
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:47,760
I play rugby.

890
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:52,640
- What's your goal in joining this show?
- I want a career in entertainment.

891
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:54,800
And I've never tried acting before.

892
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:58,200
You play such an intense sport.
Why do you speak with zero energy?

893
00:42:58,280 --> 00:42:59,720
I've been waiting a while.

894
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:02,920
His battery is low.

895
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:06,160
But he still has energy. Mew still has it.

896
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:08,640
Actually, I didn't wait long.
I'm just nervous.

897
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:11,960
I'll pass all three of you.
I want to see them walk.

898
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:13,840
I want to see all of you walk too.

899
00:43:13,920 --> 00:43:15,200
Okay, you pass.

900
00:43:15,280 --> 00:43:17,000
I'm not surprised. I knew I'd make it.

901
00:43:17,080 --> 00:43:21,200
I'm talented, determined, and hardworking.
The mentors obviously wanted to pick me.

902
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:23,440
Wait, hold on.

903
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:28,800
No, it's nothing. I agree with that.

904
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:31,000
But I want you to bring the vibe you have

905
00:43:31,080 --> 00:43:34,320
when playing the keyboard
to moments like this.

906
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:36,440
Yes, it feels like there's no energy.

907
00:43:36,520 --> 00:43:40,240
We need a good mindset because
we have to work with different people.

908
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:43,040
We have to adapt and learn.

909
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,160
Well, we'll see in the next round.

910
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:46,200
I'll do my best.

911
00:43:46,280 --> 00:43:49,080
When it comes to men,
they're very set in their ways.

912
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:52,480
Instead of listening to the new things
I'm guiding them towards.

913
00:43:52,560 --> 00:43:55,720
This group is Tarm, Heart, and Gluf.

914
00:43:56,320 --> 00:43:58,160
What's the theme? What's the concept?

915
00:43:58,240 --> 00:44:00,200
Bad boy look. We're gangsters.

916
00:44:00,280 --> 00:44:03,440
Today's story is about a gang
that grew up in the slums.

917
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:05,840
My first impression of him was good.

918
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:09,120
His strong point is having
a backstory before shooting.

919
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:11,200
Is this your actual personality?

920
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:14,360
Not this intense.
I'm overacting today to make it clear.

921
00:44:16,440 --> 00:44:18,680
Do you usually walk the runway?

922
00:44:18,760 --> 00:44:20,800
Yes. I've walked with long strides
since I was a kid.

923
00:44:20,880 --> 00:44:22,000
Since I was a toddler.

924
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:26,120
- What does that mean?
- I walk with a lot of energy.

925
00:44:26,200 --> 00:44:27,640
Like what? Can you show us?

926
00:44:28,680 --> 00:44:31,120
- Like this.
- Oh, that style.

927
00:44:31,720 --> 00:44:33,040
Do you still walk like that now?

928
00:44:33,120 --> 00:44:35,680
I walk straighter now. Fewer strides.
My health has improved.

929
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:36,800
Good health.

930
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:40,720
I have to admit, Tarm is someone who…

931
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:43,520
With him getting airtime,
the show will be fun.

932
00:44:43,600 --> 00:44:44,600
He's a real smart-ass.

933
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:47,800
Honestly,
I love that smart-ass energy of his.

934
00:44:47,880 --> 00:44:49,960
What do you think
you'll gain from <i>The Face</i>?

935
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:52,440
Probably some manners, I guess.

936
00:44:53,320 --> 00:44:54,320
See? What did I tell you?

937
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:57,280
Man, I didn't think
Tarm would be this fun.

938
00:44:57,360 --> 00:44:59,320
Looks good. He can pull it off.

939
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:01,200
We'll need to see him walk.

940
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:03,000
Gluf.

941
00:45:03,080 --> 00:45:04,440
Hello, I'm Gluf.

942
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:06,920
I've been modeling since…

943
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:08,520
I was six.

944
00:45:08,600 --> 00:45:10,720
- What?
- Wow, it has been ten years.

945
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:13,480
Did you know right away that you liked it?

946
00:45:13,560 --> 00:45:15,080
It was fun from the very first time.

947
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:18,880
And my parents supported me
because it made me happy.

948
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:20,480
I'm always happy when I walk.

949
00:45:20,560 --> 00:45:23,120
Gluf doesn't seem like someone
with a lot of energy.

950
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:26,680
I get an artist vibe from Tarm and Gluf.

951
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:30,600
If we work together,
there should be more to explore.

952
00:45:30,680 --> 00:45:33,240
For now, I pass Gluf and Tarm.

953
00:45:33,320 --> 00:45:36,920
Gluf and Tarm, you're moving on.
Congratulations.

954
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:40,840
And I'm sorry, Heart. You're not The Face.

955
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:42,920
I'm also confused about why they chose me.

956
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:45,680
Probably because
of my exceptional speaking skills.

957
00:45:45,760 --> 00:45:48,400
We've now reached the final group.

958
00:45:48,480 --> 00:45:50,480
Please bring in the final group.

959
00:45:51,080 --> 00:45:53,840
- Hello.
- Hello.

960
00:45:54,520 --> 00:45:56,360
At least the first impression is good.

961
00:45:56,440 --> 00:45:58,680
Okay, looking at their potential…

962
00:45:58,760 --> 00:46:00,440
They're exactly who we were waiting for.

963
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:03,560
The ones we waited for
are closing the show.

964
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:08,600
We've made our decision.
See you in the next round.

965
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:10,880
I'm excited and confused.

966
00:46:10,960 --> 00:46:12,640
I barely know how I made it through.

967
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:16,000
Okay, so congratulations
to Kimhan and Rome.

968
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:18,160
- Thank you.
- You're moving on to the next round.

969
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:21,920
These two…

970
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:23,640
They should be on my team.

971
00:46:23,720 --> 00:46:24,800
They really should.

972
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:26,720
I really don't like competing.

973
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:29,160
But if I have to, I don't want to lose.

974
00:46:29,240 --> 00:46:30,200
You can say whatever.

975
00:46:30,280 --> 00:46:33,160
Let them choose for themselves
which team they want.

976
00:46:44,520 --> 00:46:47,120
Welcome back to
<i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4</i>.

977
00:46:47,200 --> 00:46:49,840
And this is
the Audition Awakening runway round.

978
00:46:52,360 --> 00:46:57,360
The rules for this round are that
they will walk the runway in pairs

979
00:46:57,440 --> 00:46:59,800
while wearing caps to hide their faces.

980
00:47:00,760 --> 00:47:03,680
<i>The mentors must judge their abilities</i>
<i>based on their walk</i>

981
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:05,840
<i>and their overall presence.</i>

982
00:47:05,920 --> 00:47:08,080
<i>To pass this round,</i>

983
00:47:08,160 --> 00:47:12,640
<i>contestants need at least two votes</i>
<i>from our mentors.</i>

984
00:47:12,720 --> 00:47:15,760
Or be chosen by the Master Mentor.

985
00:47:15,840 --> 00:47:19,520
So, let's watch the runway selection.

986
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:24,360
Oh, wow.

987
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:28,840
For the first pair, I'll go with No. 2.

988
00:47:28,920 --> 00:47:32,240
Because No. 2 walks smoothly
and looks more stable.

989
00:47:32,320 --> 00:47:35,880
No. 1 walks…
His steps are a bit heavy and bouncy.

990
00:47:35,960 --> 00:47:37,920
Maybe because he can't see clearly.

991
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:41,080
So, what do the three mentors think?

992
00:47:41,160 --> 00:47:43,240
No. 1. Mentor Off, yes or no?

993
00:47:43,320 --> 00:47:45,280
- Yes.
- Yes.

994
00:47:45,360 --> 00:47:46,200
- Yes.
- I give it to both.

995
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:47,640
Okay, No. 1.

996
00:47:50,880 --> 00:47:51,800
What do you think?

997
00:47:51,880 --> 00:47:52,960
No.

998
00:47:53,040 --> 00:47:54,600
Absolutely not.

999
00:47:54,680 --> 00:47:56,800
It's a no, I'm sorry.

1000
00:47:56,880 --> 00:47:57,960
- What's wrong?
- Why?

1001
00:47:58,040 --> 00:47:59,440
We can all see No. 1.

1002
00:47:59,520 --> 00:48:01,960
He's stomping his feet like
a <i>Lord of the Rings </i>elephant.

1003
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:04,600
Hold on.

1004
00:48:04,680 --> 00:48:06,800
I said I recognize him.

1005
00:48:06,880 --> 00:48:08,760
And I think other things he brings

1006
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:10,960
are a skill set
far more valuable than this.

1007
00:48:11,040 --> 00:48:12,400
That's what I believe.

1008
00:48:12,480 --> 00:48:16,160
When he's here,
we must judge him on his talents.

1009
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:19,280
He doesn't have experience.
It's his first time.

1010
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:20,960
So, what's the verdict?

1011
00:48:21,040 --> 00:48:22,560
Do you agree, Master Mentor?

1012
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:24,560
- Sure.
- He just started.

1013
00:48:24,640 --> 00:48:26,280
- It's a yes?
- For the first pair.

1014
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:28,960
Therefore, all three mentors pass No. 1.

1015
00:48:29,040 --> 00:48:30,160
- Yes.
- Yes.

1016
00:48:37,040 --> 00:48:38,520
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

1017
00:48:38,600 --> 00:48:41,120
And No. 2, Mentors?

1018
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:42,600
- Mentor Off.
- Pass.

1019
00:48:42,680 --> 00:48:43,840
- Mentor Pancake, Mentor Ananda.
- Pass.

1020
00:48:43,920 --> 00:48:44,880
- Pass.
- Pass.

1021
00:48:44,960 --> 00:48:46,960
So, No. 2, you may take off your cap.

1022
00:48:48,240 --> 00:48:49,160
Man!

1023
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:50,400
- That's it!
- That's it!

1024
00:48:50,480 --> 00:48:52,040
Man.

1025
00:48:52,120 --> 00:48:55,520
I'm so happy.
I'll do my best in the next round.

1026
00:48:55,600 --> 00:48:58,320
Let's move right along to the second pair.

1027
00:48:58,400 --> 00:48:59,440
Second pair, come out.

1028
00:49:01,240 --> 00:49:02,440
I don't recognize them.

1029
00:49:07,520 --> 00:49:08,440
No. 3 looks better.

1030
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:10,000
No. 3's walk is smoother.

1031
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:12,960
I see that too.

1032
00:49:13,040 --> 00:49:16,120
From what we discussed, it's clear.
No. 3's walk is better.

1033
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:18,240
As you can see, No. 3 is better.

1034
00:49:18,320 --> 00:49:20,720
No. 3 passes. You can take off the cap.

1035
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:22,680
Oh, this guy.

1036
00:49:22,760 --> 00:49:23,600
What a surprise.

1037
00:49:23,680 --> 00:49:24,880
He's a survivor.

1038
00:49:24,960 --> 00:49:27,760
He told me,
"Hey, Manyoo, you're a survivor."

1039
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:29,200
I was like…

1040
00:49:29,880 --> 00:49:32,120
"Wait until I walk." How was that?

1041
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:34,040
But we still have No. 4.

1042
00:49:35,120 --> 00:49:37,040
I say no.

1043
00:49:37,120 --> 00:49:37,960
No.

1044
00:49:39,280 --> 00:49:40,880
- Mentor Off.
- I disagree.

1045
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:42,200
No. 4, take off the cap.

1046
00:49:43,440 --> 00:49:44,800
Three.

1047
00:49:45,640 --> 00:49:49,360
No. 3 was okay,
while No. 4's walk didn't really flow.

1048
00:49:49,960 --> 00:49:51,960
So I had to say goodbye.

1049
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:54,280
The runway round went exactly as expected.

1050
00:49:54,360 --> 00:49:56,800
I knew I couldn't do it.

1051
00:49:56,880 --> 00:49:58,720
Let's bring out the third pair.

1052
00:50:04,240 --> 00:50:07,560
<i>Between No. 5 and No. 6,</i>
<i>the moment they walked, No. 5 did better.</i>

1053
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:10,440
<i>Then as they got closer,</i>
<i>"Hey, I know who that is."</i>

1054
00:50:10,520 --> 00:50:13,680
<i>Knowing who they were</i>
<i>didn't make it any easier.</i>

1055
00:50:13,760 --> 00:50:15,200
<i>It made it harder.</i>

1056
00:50:15,280 --> 00:50:17,480
<i>What if I want him, but his walk is bad?</i>

1057
00:50:17,560 --> 00:50:19,360
Oh, man, total headache.

1058
00:50:19,440 --> 00:50:22,240
Anyway, right now,
I'm definitely passing No. 5.

1059
00:50:22,320 --> 00:50:23,880
Mentor Off, you're in too, right?

1060
00:50:23,960 --> 00:50:26,160
- I'm in.
- No. 5 passes.

1061
00:50:26,240 --> 00:50:28,920
No. 5 passes.
You can take off your cap, No. 5.

1062
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:32,600
- Bonus.
- Bonus.

1063
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:34,520
I passed you first.

1064
00:50:34,600 --> 00:50:35,640
Okay.

1065
00:50:35,720 --> 00:50:39,560
I've really wanted Bonus
since I saw his comp card.

1066
00:50:39,640 --> 00:50:42,800
Even with his face covered,
I recognized his charisma.

1067
00:50:42,880 --> 00:50:43,880
I want him.

1068
00:50:43,960 --> 00:50:46,480
Mile, I saw you.
This happened a few times.

1069
00:50:46,560 --> 00:50:47,440
You'll be my mentor.

1070
00:50:47,520 --> 00:50:49,440
Of course, we still have No. 6.

1071
00:50:50,440 --> 00:50:53,080
I think he can improve. I pass him.

1072
00:50:53,160 --> 00:50:54,680
There's hope. Pass.

1073
00:50:54,760 --> 00:50:55,920
I pass him.

1074
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:59,440
All three Mentors pass you.
No. 6, take off your cap.

1075
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:00,640
He's Rcha.

1076
00:51:00,720 --> 00:51:01,880
Rcha.

1077
00:51:02,680 --> 00:51:04,960
Best friends, Bonus and Rcha.

1078
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:07,600
Congratulations. You've made it through.

1079
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:09,080
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1080
00:51:09,160 --> 00:51:10,960
I'm glad. Really glad.

1081
00:51:11,040 --> 00:51:12,520
We'll go far together.

1082
00:51:12,600 --> 00:51:14,480
Let's bring out the fourth pair.

1083
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:22,240
Comparing the two in that moment,

1084
00:51:22,320 --> 00:51:26,560
my inner sense just wasn't feeling it,
so I ruled him out.

1085
00:51:26,640 --> 00:51:28,480
The second guy was better.
I didn't know who.

1086
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:30,760
I don't pass No. 7.

1087
00:51:31,800 --> 00:51:33,880
As for No. 8, I'm fine with him.

1088
00:51:33,960 --> 00:51:36,120
I disagree with Mile.

1089
00:51:36,200 --> 00:51:37,040
I say No. 7.

1090
00:51:37,120 --> 00:51:38,280
No. 7 passes.

1091
00:51:38,360 --> 00:51:40,040
No. 8 doesn't.

1092
00:51:40,120 --> 00:51:45,080
Anyway, I 100% root for No. 8 to advance.

1093
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:47,880
So let's start with No. 8.
Take off your cap.

1094
00:51:51,600 --> 00:51:55,440
And now for No. 7.
Mentor Pancake, Mentor Ananda.

1095
00:51:55,520 --> 00:51:58,600
I knew who he was,
so I judged him on his past work.

1096
00:51:58,680 --> 00:51:59,760
I pass him.

1097
00:52:00,280 --> 00:52:01,120
Okay.

1098
00:52:01,200 --> 00:52:05,000
There are some people
we can easily recognize.

1099
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:07,120
And we definitely have biases.

1100
00:52:07,200 --> 00:52:09,800
Whoever says they don't is lying.

1101
00:52:09,880 --> 00:52:13,520
No. 7 got two votes,
so you can take off your cap.

1102
00:52:14,200 --> 00:52:15,960
Thank you.

1103
00:52:16,040 --> 00:52:18,440
It's Jodbush. Congratulations.

1104
00:52:18,960 --> 00:52:22,160
I was very anxious.
At first, I didn't think I would pass.

1105
00:52:22,240 --> 00:52:25,320
Because I couldn't see much,
and I was anxious.

1106
00:52:27,320 --> 00:52:28,560
It's truly awesome.

1107
00:52:29,240 --> 00:52:31,680
I'm proud of my friend and myself.

1108
00:52:32,240 --> 00:52:35,200
Here we go.
It's only going to get more stressful.

1109
00:52:35,280 --> 00:52:37,600
Because we're now on the fifth pair.

1110
00:52:37,680 --> 00:52:39,880
So please welcome the fifth pair.

1111
00:52:55,560 --> 00:52:56,400
Both are good.

1112
00:52:56,480 --> 00:52:57,520
Mentor Off, your pick?

1113
00:52:57,600 --> 00:52:59,120
I'll pick No. 10.

1114
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:00,600
But I like No. 9.

1115
00:53:00,680 --> 00:53:02,520
Were you two enemies in a past life?

1116
00:53:02,600 --> 00:53:05,520
You've disagreed a few times now.

1117
00:53:05,600 --> 00:53:07,680
The moment No. 9 walked out,

1118
00:53:07,760 --> 00:53:12,520
are you going for a masculine
or feminine walk?

1119
00:53:12,600 --> 00:53:14,280
But when I saw No. 10,

1120
00:53:14,360 --> 00:53:18,000
I felt he looked better,
and he caught my eye more.

1121
00:53:18,640 --> 00:53:22,120
But I'm confident that in today's market,

1122
00:53:22,200 --> 00:53:27,120
this is the kind of space
where they can shine.

1123
00:53:27,200 --> 00:53:30,440
- Can you show us a feminine walk?
- Both of you.

1124
00:53:30,520 --> 00:53:31,440
Both of you.

1125
00:53:33,720 --> 00:53:35,600
Honestly, both were in between.

1126
00:53:35,680 --> 00:53:38,240
If you want to be masculine, go all out.

1127
00:53:38,320 --> 00:53:39,800
But if you want to look feminine,

1128
00:53:39,880 --> 00:53:42,320
you need more flair or make it clearer.

1129
00:53:42,400 --> 00:53:44,560
So that when compared to others,

1130
00:53:44,640 --> 00:53:48,360
I feel it wasn't strong enough
in that aspect.

1131
00:53:48,440 --> 00:53:50,680
We didn't choose anyone.

1132
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:53,640
- See?
- If we do that, it means

1133
00:53:54,160 --> 00:53:57,120
no one from this pair will advance.

1134
00:53:58,560 --> 00:54:01,560
I was the one who picked both of them.

1135
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:03,400
Now, you're throwing this burden…

1136
00:54:03,480 --> 00:54:05,360
- back on me.
- Back on you.

1137
00:54:06,800 --> 00:54:08,600
No way. I'm passing them both.

1138
00:54:09,760 --> 00:54:12,040
Take off your caps, No. 9 and No. 10.

1139
00:54:12,960 --> 00:54:16,520
Oh, yes. Congratulations.

1140
00:54:17,280 --> 00:54:21,600
Thank you, Mentors, for the chance
to make it to this round.

1141
00:54:21,680 --> 00:54:25,800
If possible, I would love
for the Mentors to consider me

1142
00:54:25,880 --> 00:54:30,640
to be part of
<i>The Face Men Thailand </i>this season.

1143
00:54:30,720 --> 00:54:33,400
All right, the sixth pair,
please step forward.

1144
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:34,880
I know who they are.

1145
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:39,000
Your hands are tense.

1146
00:54:39,080 --> 00:54:41,680
Between these two,
I think No. 12 is better.

1147
00:54:41,760 --> 00:54:44,360
Compared to the previous ones, is he okay?

1148
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:45,840
No.

1149
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:47,880
Okay, it's a no for both.

1150
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:49,960
Neither of you advances.

1151
00:54:50,040 --> 00:54:52,440
Take off your caps, No. 11 and No. 12.

1152
00:54:52,520 --> 00:54:54,520
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1153
00:54:54,600 --> 00:55:00,000
They're only 17. They might have
a lot of things to improve on.

1154
00:55:00,080 --> 00:55:01,280
Keep fighting.

1155
00:55:01,360 --> 00:55:03,120
They've only seen me twice.

1156
00:55:03,200 --> 00:55:07,720
But they don't know I have more to offer.
I'm more capable than this.

1157
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:10,120
Let's move on to the seventh pair.

1158
00:55:12,040 --> 00:55:13,800
Hey, he has a great physique.

1159
00:55:17,560 --> 00:55:21,600
Both look okay. But this guy's arms
are too stiff by his sides.

1160
00:55:21,680 --> 00:55:23,400
I would pass him.

1161
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:26,920
Unless you say
he really doesn't meet the standard.

1162
00:55:28,920 --> 00:55:30,720
I pass both.

1163
00:55:30,800 --> 00:55:31,760
All right.

1164
00:55:31,840 --> 00:55:34,080
Mentor Pancake and Mentor Ananda
pass both of you.

1165
00:55:34,160 --> 00:55:35,360
I pass them.

1166
00:55:35,440 --> 00:55:36,600
- Both of you pass.
- Yes.

1167
00:55:37,120 --> 00:55:38,520
- Passed.
- Both pass.

1168
00:55:41,360 --> 00:55:42,200
Leo.

1169
00:55:42,280 --> 00:55:43,480
Hi.

1170
00:55:52,880 --> 00:55:54,880
No. 14. Nonh.

1171
00:55:54,960 --> 00:55:58,400
Hello, I'm Nonh.
A Luang Prabang boy from Laos.

1172
00:56:00,280 --> 00:56:03,440
I like Thailand because I watch
Thai dramas and listen to Thai music.

1173
00:56:03,520 --> 00:56:06,360
I've watched <i>The Face </i>since I was a kid
and wanted to join.

1174
00:56:06,440 --> 00:56:08,320
Now that it's back, Sanonh has to be here.

1175
00:56:09,240 --> 00:56:12,200
In the past, I was a director.

1176
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:16,040
An acting coach,
and I even had my own small agency.

1177
00:56:16,120 --> 00:56:19,240
I was also a scriptwriter and a judge.

1178
00:56:19,320 --> 00:56:22,160
And a coach
on several reality shows in Laos.

1179
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:26,040
<i>Today, I'm here as a contestant again.</i>

1180
00:56:26,120 --> 00:56:30,360
<i>I'm having fun and am really excited</i>
<i>to see how this turns out.</i>

1181
00:56:30,440 --> 00:56:33,880
<i>I'm confident that joining this time</i>
<i>will give me new experiences.</i>

1182
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:36,520
<i>I'll get to do things</i>
<i>I've never done before.</i>

1183
00:56:36,600 --> 00:56:38,320
To all my fans in Laos,

1184
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:41,240
besides supporting me,
don't forget to love Thailand too.

1185
00:56:41,320 --> 00:56:44,680
Let's take a look at the next pair.
Eighth pair, please.

1186
00:56:50,720 --> 00:56:53,640
I feel like No. 16 is a bit better.

1187
00:56:53,720 --> 00:56:55,040
But I like No. 15.

1188
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:56,600
You like No. 15?

1189
00:56:56,680 --> 00:56:57,880
Mentor Mile.

1190
00:56:57,960 --> 00:56:59,960
- Only No. 15.
- Pass.

1191
00:57:01,400 --> 00:57:03,680
- Neither of you passes.
- Neither.

1192
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:06,320
That means the only one advancing is--

1193
00:57:06,400 --> 00:57:07,600
Sorry.

1194
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:11,080
I don't think either will pass.

1195
00:57:12,960 --> 00:57:15,680
So stressful.
Because anything can happen now.

1196
00:57:15,760 --> 00:57:17,560
There aren't many guys we're eyeing.

1197
00:57:17,640 --> 00:57:19,920
Yes, and now they're taking our guy out.

1198
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:21,400
Even standing right now,

1199
00:57:21,480 --> 00:57:24,640
his weight distribution
on his legs is uneven.

1200
00:57:24,720 --> 00:57:27,680
While walking, his physique doesn't help.

1201
00:57:27,760 --> 00:57:31,000
And when his brain tells him to move,
his body doesn't.

1202
00:57:31,080 --> 00:57:33,840
So I think neither of them passes.

1203
00:57:33,920 --> 00:57:36,640
- But Mentor Off's expression…
- Really?

1204
00:57:36,720 --> 00:57:39,120
I want him, so I have to get him.

1205
00:57:39,200 --> 00:57:41,560
I must do everything to get him.

1206
00:57:41,640 --> 00:57:44,640
There's still a chance
to fight for No. 15.

1207
00:57:44,720 --> 00:57:46,280
- What else do you have…
- Mentor Off, let's hear you out.

1208
00:57:46,360 --> 00:57:47,840
Besides this, do you think…

1209
00:57:48,920 --> 00:57:51,840
I feel like his journey
shouldn't end here.

1210
00:57:51,920 --> 00:57:53,880
I feel the same way. I don't…

1211
00:57:53,960 --> 00:57:57,240
I feel like he has potential, Off.
I don't know.

1212
00:57:57,320 --> 00:57:59,640
I feel this guy has a certain charisma.

1213
00:57:59,720 --> 00:58:02,360
His walk is one thing.
It wasn't that terrible.

1214
00:58:02,440 --> 00:58:03,600
But he has charisma.

1215
00:58:03,680 --> 00:58:05,720
No. 15 seems more promising.

1216
00:58:05,800 --> 00:58:07,800
This guy could be our hope.

1217
00:58:07,880 --> 00:58:10,120
I want him.
Otherwise, I wouldn't fight this hard.

1218
00:58:10,200 --> 00:58:12,200
I wouldn't fight this hard
if I didn't want him.

1219
00:58:12,280 --> 00:58:16,040
Do you realize this is the first time you
two teamed up like…

1220
00:58:16,120 --> 00:58:17,960
Mile, help me out.

1221
00:58:18,040 --> 00:58:21,080
- You two argue all the time.
- They argue all the time.

1222
00:58:21,160 --> 00:58:24,440
- Fine, I'll pass him. I give in.
- Especially lately.

1223
00:58:24,520 --> 00:58:26,640
Master Mentor Adam passes him.

1224
00:58:26,720 --> 00:58:27,680
Thank you.

1225
00:58:27,760 --> 00:58:31,520
That means No. 15, you advance.

1226
00:58:31,600 --> 00:58:33,000
Take off your cap.

1227
00:58:33,080 --> 00:58:35,200
No. 15, Rome.

1228
00:58:36,120 --> 00:58:39,000
And No. 16, you can take off your cap.

1229
00:58:39,080 --> 00:58:40,840
Hey, it's Tarm.

1230
00:58:42,040 --> 00:58:44,520
Okay, congratulations, Rome.

1231
00:58:44,600 --> 00:58:46,200
You're through to the next round.

1232
00:58:46,280 --> 00:58:49,040
I'm glad they see my potential.

1233
00:58:49,120 --> 00:58:52,880
Off is rooting for me, so I'll do my best.

1234
00:58:52,960 --> 00:58:58,560
Opportunities like this don't come often.
You have to seize it and make it happen.

1235
00:59:09,040 --> 00:59:10,800
He looks stiff. He feels stiff.

1236
00:59:10,880 --> 00:59:14,920
Between the two,
this one has the better walk.

1237
00:59:15,000 --> 00:59:15,840
Right.

1238
00:59:15,920 --> 00:59:17,560
I think it's No. 18.

1239
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:20,880
No. 17 walks like a bodybuilder.

1240
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:23,640
Clearly. It's a no-brainer.
I choose No. 18.

1241
00:59:23,720 --> 00:59:25,400
Okay, No. 18.

1242
00:59:26,400 --> 00:59:28,240
No. 18 goes through. That's three passes.

1243
00:59:28,320 --> 00:59:30,520
You advance to the next round.
Take off your cap.

1244
00:59:31,960 --> 00:59:33,320
It's Lincoln.

1245
00:59:33,840 --> 00:59:36,000
See?

1246
00:59:36,680 --> 00:59:40,240
Because these caps cover their faces,
we can't guess who they are.

1247
00:59:40,320 --> 00:59:42,720
We almost missed out on so many guys.

1248
00:59:42,800 --> 00:59:45,800
All right. That means No. 17,
you didn't make it.

1249
00:59:47,080 --> 00:59:49,000
- Superman. Good.
- That's so close.

1250
00:59:49,080 --> 00:59:55,080
I encourage my friends to be themselves
100%, and fight until the end.

1251
00:59:55,840 --> 00:59:58,320
Okay, let's move right along
to the tenth pair.

1252
00:59:58,400 --> 00:59:59,640
Tenth pair, please.

1253
01:00:04,400 --> 01:00:05,680
I like No. 20.

1254
01:00:05,760 --> 01:00:07,640
- I like No. 20 too.
- He looks relaxed.

1255
01:00:07,720 --> 01:00:09,400
No. 20 has a relaxed walk.

1256
01:00:09,480 --> 01:00:11,720
Does this mean
we're putting No. 20 through?

1257
01:00:11,800 --> 01:00:12,760
I'll pass him.

1258
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:14,880
- You're passing him?
- I like him.

1259
01:00:14,960 --> 01:00:16,840
- No. 20 is through?
- Yes, No. 20.

1260
01:00:16,920 --> 01:00:18,480
No. 20, take off your cap.

1261
01:00:20,960 --> 01:00:22,200
- Hello.
- Hello.

1262
01:00:22,280 --> 01:00:23,440
It's Safe.

1263
01:00:23,520 --> 01:00:26,160
All right, and as for No. 19…

1264
01:00:26,240 --> 01:00:27,440
I'm voting no on No. 19.

1265
01:00:27,520 --> 01:00:28,560
Yes, I agree.

1266
01:00:28,640 --> 01:00:30,240
Yes, we're all on the same page.

1267
01:00:30,320 --> 01:00:32,680
No. 19, you can take off your cap.

1268
01:00:34,560 --> 01:00:35,560
I get it.

1269
01:00:35,640 --> 01:00:40,000
You might still need a lot of time
to improve yourself.

1270
01:00:40,080 --> 01:00:43,280
If you really want this,
we'll see your effort.

1271
01:00:43,360 --> 01:00:46,120
I won't give up.
I'll definitely come back again.

1272
01:00:46,200 --> 01:00:47,560
The 11th pair, please.

1273
01:00:50,600 --> 01:00:52,200
Oh, wow.

1274
01:00:52,280 --> 01:00:54,840
Wow, his walk is really eye-catching.

1275
01:00:54,920 --> 01:00:59,360
Wow, compared to him,
No. 22 doesn't stand a chance.

1276
01:00:59,440 --> 01:01:02,560
I think No. 21 is showing us
that he has two walking styles.

1277
01:01:02,640 --> 01:01:03,520
Yes, clearly.

1278
01:01:03,600 --> 01:01:06,800
Because his first walk was very masculine.

1279
01:01:06,880 --> 01:01:09,280
But on his second walk,
he tried to show us that…

1280
01:01:09,360 --> 01:01:11,760
It's a trick, and I don't really like it.

1281
01:01:12,760 --> 01:01:15,280
I call it the firework trick.
That's the term I use.

1282
01:01:15,360 --> 01:01:17,920
It's like shooting a firework,
so we look up at it.

1283
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:19,920
Then we forget what else is happening.

1284
01:01:20,000 --> 01:01:22,520
Some Mentors might go,
"Oh, that's so good."

1285
01:01:22,600 --> 01:01:25,720
Master Mentor actually said
he doesn't like tricks like this.

1286
01:01:25,800 --> 01:01:27,840
But I want him on my team,
so I don't mind it.

1287
01:01:27,920 --> 01:01:33,120
No hard feelings,
but it's just not how I judge.

1288
01:01:33,200 --> 01:01:37,840
That means No. 21 gets a pass.
From all three Mentors.

1289
01:01:37,920 --> 01:01:40,680
All right, No. 21,
you can take off your cap.

1290
01:01:40,760 --> 01:01:42,320
- It's Honda.
- Okay.

1291
01:01:42,400 --> 01:01:45,240
- No. 22, you didn't pass.
- Mentor Mile?

1292
01:01:45,320 --> 01:01:46,960
- Mentor Off?
- No.

1293
01:01:47,040 --> 01:01:49,160
You didn't make it.
You can take off your cap, No. 22.

1294
01:01:49,960 --> 01:01:50,960
It's Arm.

1295
01:01:51,600 --> 01:01:53,160
Arm, you're not The Face yet.

1296
01:01:53,240 --> 01:01:55,080
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1297
01:01:55,160 --> 01:01:56,120
Thank you.

1298
01:01:56,200 --> 01:01:58,840
Let's move right along to the 12th pair.

1299
01:01:58,920 --> 01:02:00,760
The 12th pair, please.

1300
01:02:02,840 --> 01:02:06,920
Right now, I feel like
No. 23 has the better walk.

1301
01:02:07,000 --> 01:02:10,280
As soon as No. 23 walked out,
I could see his confidence.

1302
01:02:10,360 --> 01:02:12,480
I saw a solid walk.

1303
01:02:12,560 --> 01:02:14,360
I'm putting No. 23 through.

1304
01:02:14,440 --> 01:02:17,200
Yes, I think it's clear No. 23 is better.

1305
01:02:17,280 --> 01:02:19,480
No. 23, you can take off your cap.

1306
01:02:20,680 --> 01:02:22,680
- Oh, yeah.
- This is Peem.

1307
01:02:22,760 --> 01:02:24,920
And what about No. 24?

1308
01:02:25,000 --> 01:02:26,480
- No.
- No.

1309
01:02:26,560 --> 01:02:28,360
- Mentor Mile says no?
- No pass.

1310
01:02:28,440 --> 01:02:31,120
Mentor Pancake, Mentor Ananda, no pass.

1311
01:02:31,760 --> 01:02:33,760
No. 24, you can take off your cap.

1312
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:36,360
Oh, Gluf.

1313
01:02:37,960 --> 01:02:39,920
It's a shame about Gluf.
He didn't make it.

1314
01:02:40,000 --> 01:02:42,080
I don't know what to say.

1315
01:02:42,160 --> 01:02:44,160
It's a pity. I still feel bad about it.

1316
01:02:44,240 --> 01:02:47,520
Well, if there's a chance in the future…

1317
01:02:47,600 --> 01:02:50,080
You'll probably see me on <i>The Face </i>again.

1318
01:02:50,160 --> 01:02:51,520
I'll definitely be back.

1319
01:02:53,800 --> 01:02:55,040
Taking long strides.

1320
01:02:59,680 --> 01:03:01,640
This pair had the lowest energy.

1321
01:03:01,720 --> 01:03:05,360
They both walked like they were tiptoeing.

1322
01:03:05,440 --> 01:03:08,120
Are we passing No. 25?

1323
01:03:09,040 --> 01:03:11,440
- No.
- So No. 25 doesn't pass.

1324
01:03:11,520 --> 01:03:13,320
No. 25, you can take off your cap.

1325
01:03:16,960 --> 01:03:18,880
All right, Dan.

1326
01:03:20,480 --> 01:03:22,280
You have a say, don't you?

1327
01:03:22,360 --> 01:03:24,600
- Wait, hold on.
- He took off his cap.

1328
01:03:24,680 --> 01:03:27,160
Hey, do you realize
your shoulders are uneven?

1329
01:03:27,240 --> 01:03:30,440
The doctor didn't say they were uneven.

1330
01:03:30,520 --> 01:03:33,040
But it's probably
because I play badminton.

1331
01:03:34,680 --> 01:03:36,280
What about No. 26?

1332
01:03:36,360 --> 01:03:38,440
I'm fine with his walk.

1333
01:03:38,520 --> 01:03:40,720
But sometimes, his steps feel a bit…

1334
01:03:41,720 --> 01:03:45,520
- Like he's bouncing on his heels.
- It's supposed to be a catwalk.

1335
01:03:45,600 --> 01:03:49,520
- Can we see it again? Walk again.
- It can be fixed. No. 26, one more time.

1336
01:03:51,920 --> 01:03:54,400
I think men's walks are quite simple.

1337
01:03:54,480 --> 01:03:57,280
We want them to look smart and natural.

1338
01:03:57,360 --> 01:03:59,720
And be energetic in their steps.

1339
01:03:59,800 --> 01:04:01,320
That's really all it takes.

1340
01:04:01,400 --> 01:04:02,320
I'll take No. 26.

1341
01:04:02,400 --> 01:04:04,760
- Mentor Pancake chooses No. 26.
- Sure.

1342
01:04:04,840 --> 01:04:06,280
- I think it works.
- No. 26.

1343
01:04:06,360 --> 01:04:08,840
Master Mentor, can I have Dan too?

1344
01:04:10,200 --> 01:04:13,480
<i>Dan said we can adjust his posture</i>
<i>since it's not a bone issue.</i>

1345
01:04:13,560 --> 01:04:15,240
<i>Okay, that's a relief.</i>

1346
01:04:15,760 --> 01:04:19,840
So I took the chance
to ask the Master Mentor.

1347
01:04:19,920 --> 01:04:22,040
- I don't know.
- I'll allow it.

1348
01:04:22,120 --> 01:04:24,120
Oh, wow.

1349
01:04:24,200 --> 01:04:27,320
Congratulations.
You're through to the next round.

1350
01:04:28,240 --> 01:04:30,680
And just now, No. 26 also passed.

1351
01:04:30,760 --> 01:04:32,320
No. 26, take off your cap.

1352
01:04:34,280 --> 01:04:37,720
Hello, I'm PP,
Pattanaphong Phattanakaphun.

1353
01:04:37,800 --> 01:04:40,440
I'm currently studying
at Thammasat University.

1354
01:04:40,520 --> 01:04:41,600
I'm a sophomore.

1355
01:04:41,680 --> 01:04:45,320
<i>I balance sports, studies, and music.</i>

1356
01:04:45,400 --> 01:04:47,920
<i>And I'm also a freelance model.</i>

1357
01:04:48,000 --> 01:04:51,080
<i>I've played rugby for nine years.</i>

1358
01:04:51,160 --> 01:04:53,840
<i>I think I've been pretty successful at it.</i>

1359
01:04:53,920 --> 01:04:55,200
<i>Coming to this show,</i>

1360
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:58,400
<i>I want to be as successful</i>
<i>as I am in rugby.</i>

1361
01:04:58,960 --> 01:05:01,480
Joining <i>The Face Men</i>…

1362
01:05:01,560 --> 01:05:03,200
I have to be The Face.

1363
01:05:03,280 --> 01:05:04,920
The 14th pair, please come out.

1364
01:05:10,280 --> 01:05:11,280
Again.

1365
01:05:11,360 --> 01:05:13,760
- Everyone wants him.
- Same here.

1366
01:05:13,840 --> 01:05:14,920
What should we do?

1367
01:05:15,880 --> 01:05:18,880
<i>As soon as No. 27 walked out,</i>
<i>we knew who he was.</i>

1368
01:05:18,960 --> 01:05:20,680
<i>We had high expectations.</i>

1369
01:05:20,760 --> 01:05:23,000
<i>Everyone said he was great,</i>
<i>and we wanted him.</i>

1370
01:05:23,080 --> 01:05:24,360
So what happened?

1371
01:05:24,440 --> 01:05:27,280
It was so bad, I was shocked.

1372
01:05:27,360 --> 01:05:29,480
I was just completely confused.

1373
01:05:29,560 --> 01:05:31,840
- Let's give feedback.
- Can I have the good news first?

1374
01:05:31,920 --> 01:05:33,040
I really like No. 28.

1375
01:05:33,120 --> 01:05:35,200
- No. 28 works.
- No. 28 is great.

1376
01:05:35,280 --> 01:05:37,920
All Mentors pass No. 28.
Take off your cap.

1377
01:05:38,000 --> 01:05:39,680
Hello.

1378
01:05:39,760 --> 01:05:40,800
Jimmy.

1379
01:05:40,880 --> 01:05:43,120
Congratulations. You made it.

1380
01:05:43,200 --> 01:05:45,680
Now, we still have No. 27.

1381
01:05:45,760 --> 01:05:48,280
- I don't think the catwalk is for him.
- Yes, it's not…

1382
01:05:48,360 --> 01:05:50,680
This might not be his strong suit.

1383
01:05:50,760 --> 01:05:54,200
But in the previous round,
we didn't see him walk like this.

1384
01:05:55,040 --> 01:05:59,200
It was unexpected.
We didn't anticipate this.

1385
01:05:59,280 --> 01:06:04,560
His walk, how he drops his hips,
and his footwork looked…

1386
01:06:04,640 --> 01:06:06,880
It didn't look like a man's walk.

1387
01:06:06,960 --> 01:06:10,880
If there was another challenge
and we gave him tighter direction…

1388
01:06:10,960 --> 01:06:13,840
And you had to be perfect,
I would use that right.

1389
01:06:13,920 --> 01:06:16,000
I feel like… I don't know how to decide.

1390
01:06:16,080 --> 01:06:17,600
There are no more chances, right?

1391
01:06:17,680 --> 01:06:19,880
- The next round is the final selection.
- Yes.

1392
01:06:19,960 --> 01:06:21,240
I'll pass him for now.

1393
01:06:21,320 --> 01:06:22,560
That's one vote to pass.

1394
01:06:22,640 --> 01:06:25,280
You need one more vote
to make it to the next round.

1395
01:06:25,360 --> 01:06:27,200
Mentor Mile, Mentor Off.

1396
01:06:27,280 --> 01:06:30,000
No. 27's fate is in your hands.

1397
01:06:30,080 --> 01:06:31,560
I don't want to lose this guy.

1398
01:06:31,640 --> 01:06:35,160
If we pass him,
the audience will definitely criticize me.

1399
01:06:35,240 --> 01:06:37,760
Wondering why I let him in
over better candidates.

1400
01:06:37,840 --> 01:06:40,080
But at that moment,
I just had to have him.

1401
01:06:42,080 --> 01:06:44,000
- Mentor Off passes him.
- I'll keep him.

1402
01:06:44,080 --> 01:06:45,960
- Mentor Mile.
- He already has two.

1403
01:06:46,040 --> 01:06:48,000
Right, two out of three is enough.

1404
01:06:48,080 --> 01:06:49,040
So he passes.

1405
01:06:49,120 --> 01:06:50,760
No. 27, take off your cap.

1406
01:06:51,880 --> 01:06:52,920
Kimhan.

1407
01:06:54,440 --> 01:06:55,800
<i>I made it through, but…</i>

1408
01:06:55,880 --> 01:06:58,240
<i>It feels somewhat bittersweet.</i>

1409
01:07:01,640 --> 01:07:02,720
I'm speechless.

1410
01:07:04,720 --> 01:07:08,040
I'm more disappointed in myself.

1411
01:07:09,160 --> 01:07:12,000
Let's move on to our 15th pair.

1412
01:07:14,160 --> 01:07:18,280
Hey, they're both great.
How do they look so good together?

1413
01:07:18,360 --> 01:07:21,640
I don't think No. 30 stands out that much.

1414
01:07:21,720 --> 01:07:23,080
He could stay or go.

1415
01:07:23,160 --> 01:07:25,240
If you ask who's better, I'd say No. 29.

1416
01:07:25,320 --> 01:07:27,160
I agree on No. 29.

1417
01:07:27,240 --> 01:07:29,800
- No. 29 is better.
- Yes, No. 29 is better.

1418
01:07:29,880 --> 01:07:31,640
No. 29, take off your cap.

1419
01:07:32,200 --> 01:07:34,160
- Wow.
- This is Fox.

1420
01:07:35,160 --> 01:07:36,160
Looking tough.

1421
01:07:36,240 --> 01:07:37,600
You're hard to kill.

1422
01:07:37,680 --> 01:07:39,640
- Great walk.
- You're hard to kill.

1423
01:07:39,720 --> 01:07:43,800
What about No. 30?
Will the mentors let him through?

1424
01:07:43,880 --> 01:07:45,640
- Yes.
- He passes.

1425
01:07:45,720 --> 01:07:47,040
All three mentors pass you.

1426
01:07:47,120 --> 01:07:48,520
No. 30, take off your cap.

1427
01:07:49,280 --> 01:07:50,760
- Jacob.
- Hey, handsome.

1428
01:07:50,840 --> 01:07:52,320
Oh, Jacob.

1429
01:07:52,400 --> 01:07:53,680
You're both hard to kill.

1430
01:07:53,760 --> 01:07:54,920
Both of you.

1431
01:07:55,000 --> 01:07:56,200
I was under a lot of pressure.

1432
01:07:56,280 --> 01:07:59,320
Last round,
everyone wanted to see me walk.

1433
01:07:59,400 --> 01:08:01,880
So I decided to save the best for later.

1434
01:08:01,960 --> 01:08:04,480
- See?
- See?

1435
01:08:04,560 --> 01:08:06,920
You proved me wrong. You really did.

1436
01:08:07,000 --> 01:08:08,960
You beat me this round.

1437
01:08:10,400 --> 01:08:12,200
I'm thrilled because…

1438
01:08:15,720 --> 01:08:17,200
The 16th pair, step forward.

1439
01:08:19,439 --> 01:08:23,000
No. 32, I think he started off a bit weak.

1440
01:08:23,080 --> 01:08:27,200
Especially paired with No. 31.
No. 31 looks like a real fashion model.

1441
01:08:27,279 --> 01:08:28,399
Straight off the runway.

1442
01:08:28,479 --> 01:08:30,760
If I compare the two of you…

1443
01:08:30,840 --> 01:08:33,240
No. 31 walked better.

1444
01:08:33,319 --> 01:08:34,760
I choose No. 31 too.

1445
01:08:34,840 --> 01:08:36,960
- Same here.
- Yes, No. 31.

1446
01:08:37,040 --> 01:08:39,160
As for No. 32, it seems…

1447
01:08:39,240 --> 01:08:41,439
I think it comes back to your legs again.

1448
01:08:41,520 --> 01:08:43,240
- Same as before.
- It's your feet.

1449
01:08:43,319 --> 01:08:44,520
- Let's look.
- The pacing…

1450
01:08:44,600 --> 01:08:45,920
Can we see him walk again?

1451
01:08:47,560 --> 01:08:49,520
This is better.

1452
01:08:49,600 --> 01:08:52,240
I asked him to walk again.
He corrected himself well.

1453
01:08:52,319 --> 01:08:54,920
These are the kinds of people
I want on my team.

1454
01:08:55,000 --> 01:08:56,640
Can we pass No. 32?

1455
01:08:56,720 --> 01:08:58,960
- Yes, he passes.
- Sure, No. 32 passes.

1456
01:08:59,040 --> 01:09:00,479
- Pass.
- Pass.

1457
01:09:03,359 --> 01:09:06,240
Luca and Mew.

1458
01:09:06,319 --> 01:09:08,200
Congratulations,

1459
01:09:08,279 --> 01:09:09,399
Mew and Luca.

1460
01:09:13,560 --> 01:09:15,720
Three passes this round. Next round…

1461
01:09:19,200 --> 01:09:21,560
That was the final pair

1462
01:09:21,640 --> 01:09:24,800
of our runway auditions.

1463
01:09:24,880 --> 01:09:26,600
From the recent auditions,

1464
01:09:26,680 --> 01:09:30,000
we narrowed it down from 32 contestants.

1465
01:09:30,080 --> 01:09:33,040
Now, only 24 remain.

1466
01:09:33,120 --> 01:09:35,399
We haven't even picked teams yet,

1467
01:09:35,479 --> 01:09:37,920
and we're already so torn
about letting people go.

1468
01:09:38,000 --> 01:09:43,800
Next, we're moving on
to the Team Selection round.

1469
01:09:43,880 --> 01:09:45,200
So right now,

1470
01:09:45,279 --> 01:09:47,640
our mentors can go get ready.

1471
01:09:47,720 --> 01:09:51,120
<i>I have a clear picture of the team I want.</i>

1472
01:09:51,200 --> 01:09:52,840
It can't just be anyone.

1473
01:09:52,920 --> 01:09:54,960
It must be people with real potential.

1474
01:09:55,040 --> 01:09:58,000
And if it comes together,
my team will be terrifying.

1475
01:09:58,080 --> 01:09:59,600
More importantly,

1476
01:09:59,680 --> 01:10:01,560
I need to get them on my team first.

1477
01:10:09,960 --> 01:10:13,040
We've now reached
the final audition round.

1478
01:10:13,120 --> 01:10:14,760
The Team Selection.

1479
01:10:14,840 --> 01:10:16,360
In this Team Selection round,

1480
01:10:16,440 --> 01:10:19,840
the mentors must pick contestants
for their teams.

1481
01:10:19,920 --> 01:10:24,080
If a mentor is interested in a contestant,
hold up your modeling book.

1482
01:10:24,160 --> 01:10:27,680
But if more than one mentor
holds up their book,

1483
01:10:27,760 --> 01:10:31,320
the contestant gets to choose their team.

1484
01:10:31,400 --> 01:10:34,800
This season,
each mentor gets five team members.

1485
01:10:34,880 --> 01:10:38,960
However, mentors can only pick
four of them.

1486
01:10:39,040 --> 01:10:41,280
For the final spot,

1487
01:10:41,360 --> 01:10:44,000
our Master Mentor will pick for you.

1488
01:10:44,080 --> 01:10:47,560
I really hope
the interesting ones get picked.

1489
01:10:47,640 --> 01:10:51,120
You might be happy,
disappointed, or stressed out.

1490
01:10:51,200 --> 01:10:52,840
We'll have to wait and see.

1491
01:10:54,080 --> 01:10:55,560
I'm going with the flow now.

1492
01:10:55,640 --> 01:10:57,640
Whoever joins my team is meant to be.

1493
01:10:57,720 --> 01:11:01,000
I believe everything is predestined.
Let's do this.

1494
01:11:01,080 --> 01:11:02,520
- Is everyone ready?
- Ready.

1495
01:11:02,600 --> 01:11:05,520
If you're ready,
let's begin the Team Selection.

1496
01:11:05,600 --> 01:11:09,320
Just relax, because ultimately, our job is

1497
01:11:09,400 --> 01:11:11,520
to do whatever it takes
to get who we want.

1498
01:11:11,600 --> 01:11:12,960
That's it.

1499
01:11:13,040 --> 01:11:17,840
In terms of experience and airtime,
we're second to none.

1500
01:11:17,920 --> 01:11:20,640
If you want real skills,
you should join our team.

1501
01:11:20,720 --> 01:11:22,400
Just wait and see.

1502
01:11:22,480 --> 01:11:26,360
I'm not that great, but I'm pretty good
at snatching things up.

1503
01:11:27,680 --> 01:11:29,640
Please welcome the first person, Kimhan.

1504
01:11:32,520 --> 01:11:33,440
I'm raising mine.

1505
01:11:33,520 --> 01:11:34,600
I raise.

1506
01:11:34,680 --> 01:11:36,680
Okay, I raise mine too.

1507
01:11:36,760 --> 01:11:37,960
Open the door.

1508
01:11:40,720 --> 01:11:43,240
<i>I'm relieved. I feel so relieved.</i>

1509
01:11:43,320 --> 01:11:44,800
<i>But also stressed.</i>

1510
01:11:44,880 --> 01:11:46,440
I don't know who to choose.

1511
01:11:46,520 --> 01:11:49,720
Since the competition started,
I talked to Mentor Pancake about him.

1512
01:11:49,800 --> 01:11:52,480
- He was our top pick, right?
- Right.

1513
01:11:52,560 --> 01:11:54,400
And we were always ready to pass you.

1514
01:11:54,480 --> 01:11:57,200
We only doubted you on the runway.

1515
01:11:57,280 --> 01:12:00,080
I was shocked.
Can you tell me what happened that day?

1516
01:12:00,160 --> 01:12:02,760
I was probably putting pressure on myself.

1517
01:12:02,840 --> 01:12:04,960
And my hip hurt, and…

1518
01:12:05,040 --> 01:12:07,960
It was a combination of things.
I'll take the blame.

1519
01:12:08,040 --> 01:12:10,360
- You understand that…
- I completely understand.

1520
01:12:10,440 --> 01:12:13,880
- I believe you can do better.
- I'm very confident I can do better.

1521
01:12:13,960 --> 01:12:16,000
I believe you.
That's why I was the first to raise.

1522
01:12:16,080 --> 01:12:19,520
I practically begged Adam
to get you here. That's it.

1523
01:12:20,240 --> 01:12:23,120
I'm glad because he's someone
who always fought for me.

1524
01:12:23,200 --> 01:12:27,240
The chance Off gave me
means the world to me.

1525
01:12:27,320 --> 01:12:29,960
Are you sure he really wants you?

1526
01:12:30,040 --> 01:12:31,880
He could just be provoking me.

1527
01:12:31,960 --> 01:12:35,560
But just now, Menter Off picked you.

1528
01:12:35,640 --> 01:12:36,960
- He raised the book first.
- First.

1529
01:12:37,040 --> 01:12:39,240
Flowers don't matter
because they'll wither.

1530
01:12:39,320 --> 01:12:43,160
I don't know. I just brought them
to welcome our new member.

1531
01:12:43,240 --> 01:12:47,000
They don't last forever, true.
But a beginning always has to happen.

1532
01:12:47,080 --> 01:12:49,960
<i>I can't believe</i>
<i>I picked exactly six flowers.</i>

1533
01:12:50,040 --> 01:12:53,200
For Ananda, me,
and the incoming new members.

1534
01:12:53,280 --> 01:12:55,520
So, let's wait and see…

1535
01:12:55,600 --> 01:12:57,520
who gets the flower.

1536
01:12:59,720 --> 01:13:01,720
Why did she bring that?

1537
01:13:02,360 --> 01:13:04,200
Why is she holding that?

1538
01:13:05,440 --> 01:13:08,160
With props around,
anything bizarre may happen.

1539
01:13:08,240 --> 01:13:10,440
Is she trying to win him over?
I'm worried.

1540
01:13:10,520 --> 01:13:12,080
We don't have any flowers.

1541
01:13:13,000 --> 01:13:14,280
Can we get a whole tree?

1542
01:13:14,360 --> 01:13:16,160
Don't fight over him.
Why are you doing this?

1543
01:13:16,240 --> 01:13:19,440
I can give you everything.
Come on. Join me.

1544
01:13:19,520 --> 01:13:20,520
Can I ask a question?

1545
01:13:20,600 --> 01:13:22,800
- Go ahead.
- Ask away.

1546
01:13:22,880 --> 01:13:24,960
I would like to ask all the Mentors

1547
01:13:25,040 --> 01:13:27,040
what strengths do you see in me?

1548
01:13:27,120 --> 01:13:29,800
And how would you help me grow?

1549
01:13:29,880 --> 01:13:32,960
Honestly, I just wanted to be involved.

1550
01:13:33,040 --> 01:13:36,120
Because I think you're a good fit for Off.

1551
01:13:36,200 --> 01:13:37,400
So I'm helping him out.

1552
01:13:37,480 --> 01:13:39,800
But if you want a true role model,

1553
01:13:39,880 --> 01:13:41,360
come to this side.

1554
01:13:41,440 --> 01:13:44,040
I think that side
can offer you some sassiness.

1555
01:13:46,040 --> 01:13:50,520
The reason I'm serious
and speaking honestly to you is

1556
01:13:50,600 --> 01:13:52,880
I have the skills to offer you.

1557
01:13:52,960 --> 01:13:56,800
You're interested in fashion and modeling.

1558
01:13:58,040 --> 01:13:59,480
You've got the top right here.

1559
01:13:59,560 --> 01:14:01,880
Acting, movies,
I'm ready to offer you that.

1560
01:14:01,960 --> 01:14:03,640
I'm ready to offer you that too.

1561
01:14:03,720 --> 01:14:05,360
- Offer you the sassiness.
- Offer you everything.

1562
01:14:05,880 --> 01:14:07,080
Tell me what you want.

1563
01:14:07,760 --> 01:14:09,880
I also have my own community.

1564
01:14:09,960 --> 01:14:13,560
I have hundreds of juniors at Grammy. I…

1565
01:14:14,080 --> 01:14:15,840
Oops, was that too harsh? Sorry.

1566
01:14:15,920 --> 01:14:18,880
Off, wait.
Can you really take care of hundreds?

1567
01:14:18,960 --> 01:14:20,400
- About 170 people.
- 170.

1568
01:14:20,480 --> 01:14:21,760
People in my agency right now.

1569
01:14:21,840 --> 01:14:27,080
Get as much experience as I have,
then call me. We'll talk.

1570
01:14:28,960 --> 01:14:30,640
Okay, got it.

1571
01:14:30,720 --> 01:14:33,120
It will take me another 16 years
to match your experience.

1572
01:14:33,200 --> 01:14:36,240
By then,
you'll probably be a National Artist.

1573
01:14:36,320 --> 01:14:38,560
Okay, I'll call you then.

1574
01:14:38,640 --> 01:14:40,640
Will you have the strength
to pick up a phone by then?

1575
01:14:40,720 --> 01:14:42,360
So, Kimhan.

1576
01:14:42,880 --> 01:14:44,800
Which team do you choose?

1577
01:14:45,600 --> 01:14:47,960
I choose team…

1578
01:14:51,720 --> 01:14:53,440
Ananda and Pancake.

1579
01:14:57,160 --> 01:14:59,760
- Off.
- Go ahead, kid.

1580
01:14:59,840 --> 01:15:01,720
Just don't end up in the Black Room.

1581
01:15:01,800 --> 01:15:03,720
Congratulations to Kimhan.

1582
01:15:03,800 --> 01:15:06,320
You're on Mentor Ananda
and Mentor Pancake's team.

1583
01:15:07,080 --> 01:15:10,920
Honestly, if Off had fought a bit harder,
I might have picked him.

1584
01:15:11,000 --> 01:15:14,160
If he had fought just a little more,
I really might have.

1585
01:15:14,240 --> 01:15:16,520
I'd better not see Kimhan
in the Black Room,

1586
01:15:16,600 --> 01:15:19,520
because he is definitely going home first.

1587
01:15:19,600 --> 01:15:20,800
Next person, please.

1588
01:15:21,760 --> 01:15:22,880
Marilyn.

1589
01:15:24,640 --> 01:15:26,240
Please, pick me.

1590
01:15:26,320 --> 01:15:28,040
- Okay, I've decided.
- Same.

1591
01:15:28,120 --> 01:15:29,640
You may raise your modeling books now.

1592
01:15:34,360 --> 01:15:37,280
I'm sorry. You're not The Face.

1593
01:15:37,360 --> 01:15:38,640
<i>I feel empty.</i>

1594
01:15:39,240 --> 01:15:43,360
I don't understand why.
Why couldn't I be there?

1595
01:15:43,440 --> 01:15:44,720
He looks so disappointed.

1596
01:15:44,800 --> 01:15:46,760
It's not that he's bad.
I want to give him a chance.

1597
01:15:46,840 --> 01:15:48,600
I see his potential.

1598
01:15:48,680 --> 01:15:52,800
But I don't think
this is the best fit for him right now.

1599
01:15:52,880 --> 01:15:54,880
Let's move on to the next person.

1600
01:15:54,960 --> 01:15:56,000
Peem.

1601
01:15:58,600 --> 01:16:00,960
If the Mentors are ready,
you may raise your books.

1602
01:16:02,800 --> 01:16:04,120
I like this guy.

1603
01:16:04,200 --> 01:16:05,280
Open the door.

1604
01:16:07,840 --> 01:16:11,840
Congratulations, Peem.
Two teams chose you.

1605
01:16:11,920 --> 01:16:13,360
Team Off and Team Mile.

1606
01:16:13,440 --> 01:16:15,440
- Are you nervous?
- I've got goosebumps.

1607
01:16:16,080 --> 01:16:17,160
I'm very nervous. So nervous.

1608
01:16:17,240 --> 01:16:19,520
<i>I feel like Peem</i>
<i>has something I connect with.</i>

1609
01:16:19,600 --> 01:16:24,040
I want to see his other unique qualities.

1610
01:16:24,120 --> 01:16:27,000
I want him to present
and show them to everyone.

1611
01:16:27,080 --> 01:16:28,720
I think Peem has a lot to offer.

1612
01:16:28,800 --> 01:16:30,640
I saw you singing and checked it out.

1613
01:16:30,720 --> 01:16:34,760
I saw you playing guitar and many things
that show your sense of groove.

1614
01:16:34,840 --> 01:16:38,160
I like your presentation style.

1615
01:16:38,240 --> 01:16:40,080
- And you study Comm Arts, right?
- Yes.

1616
01:16:40,160 --> 01:16:41,360
I studied Journalism.

1617
01:16:41,440 --> 01:16:42,760
I went to
Triam Udom Suksa School back then.

1618
01:16:43,640 --> 01:16:45,800
- Building 3 is right next door.
- We were close.

1619
01:16:45,880 --> 01:16:48,280
I'd always cross over
to eat at the canteen.

1620
01:16:48,360 --> 01:16:49,760
I love the students' vibe.

1621
01:16:49,840 --> 01:16:51,120
- Is he…
- Yeah.

1622
01:16:51,200 --> 01:16:52,360
We're like brothers.

1623
01:16:52,440 --> 01:16:54,000
You're trying really hard.

1624
01:16:54,080 --> 01:16:55,840
- Fight for him!
- Just take him!

1625
01:16:55,920 --> 01:17:00,440
As soon as Peem walked out,
I knew he would choose Team Mile.

1626
01:17:00,520 --> 01:17:03,400
I didn't know how to fight that.
I was just smiling at him.

1627
01:17:04,680 --> 01:17:06,360
All right, Peem.

1628
01:17:06,440 --> 01:17:07,840
Which team are you choosing?

1629
01:17:07,920 --> 01:17:11,840
Thank you both so much,
and also Ananda and Pancake.

1630
01:17:17,200 --> 01:17:20,000
But ultimately, I think

1631
01:17:20,080 --> 01:17:24,640
I want to choose the team
where I can best envision my future.

1632
01:17:24,720 --> 01:17:25,760
You don't even look at me.

1633
01:17:27,520 --> 01:17:30,360
So I would like to choose Team Mile.

1634
01:17:30,880 --> 01:17:32,160
Perfect fit.

1635
01:17:32,240 --> 01:17:33,080
He's good.

1636
01:17:35,320 --> 01:17:37,160
<i>Peem has an interesting personality.</i>

1637
01:17:37,240 --> 01:17:38,800
<i>I like him too.</i>

1638
01:17:38,880 --> 01:17:42,000
I hope I don't see my favorites
in the Black Room. That's all.

1639
01:17:42,080 --> 01:17:44,840
Well, Off is going to have
a hard time too.

1640
01:17:44,920 --> 01:17:46,240
You'd better be prepared, Off.

1641
01:17:46,320 --> 01:17:48,400
Next up, Lincoln.

1642
01:17:53,560 --> 01:17:54,960
Hey.

1643
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:56,920
I raised my book immediately because…

1644
01:17:57,000 --> 01:17:58,480
- His charisma.
- He's charming.

1645
01:17:58,560 --> 01:18:00,160
I think he's very versatile.

1646
01:18:00,240 --> 01:18:01,840
- Hello.
- Hello.

1647
01:18:03,840 --> 01:18:05,960
- Welcome.
- Hello.

1648
01:18:06,040 --> 01:18:09,440
Lincoln is now
with Team Pancake and Ananda.

1649
01:18:09,520 --> 01:18:11,000
Please root for us.

1650
01:18:13,280 --> 01:18:14,880
Next up, Nonh.

1651
01:18:17,760 --> 01:18:19,840
I'm sorry, but you are not The Face.

1652
01:18:19,920 --> 01:18:23,840
I'm disappointed.
I didn't expect this to happen.

1653
01:18:23,920 --> 01:18:27,120
Because all four mentors chose me
in the last two rounds.

1654
01:18:27,200 --> 01:18:30,000
I never thought anyone
would pick me today.

1655
01:18:30,080 --> 01:18:32,160
Next up, Honda. Open the doors.

1656
01:18:34,120 --> 01:18:36,320
I'm sorry, but you are not The Face.

1657
01:18:36,400 --> 01:18:39,680
<i>I want to say to Pancake,</i>
<i>we've worked together before.</i>

1658
01:18:39,760 --> 01:18:42,160
You should know my potential.

1659
01:18:42,240 --> 01:18:43,720
I was expecting you to pick me.

1660
01:18:43,800 --> 01:18:45,840
Next up, Jodbush.

1661
01:18:47,000 --> 01:18:49,440
I'm sorry. You are not The Face.

1662
01:18:49,520 --> 01:18:50,560
Thank you very much.

1663
01:18:50,640 --> 01:18:55,480
I'm a bit disappointed.
I wasn't prepared to go home.

1664
01:18:55,560 --> 01:18:58,440
<i>It's a shame we had to let Jodbush go.</i>

1665
01:18:58,520 --> 01:19:01,840
He has a great personality,
but he's already an influencer.

1666
01:19:01,920 --> 01:19:04,480
He's on social media.
I'm not sure what to do with him.

1667
01:19:04,560 --> 01:19:06,120
He already seems established.

1668
01:19:06,200 --> 01:19:08,880
I personally like him a lot. I feel like…

1669
01:19:08,960 --> 01:19:12,160
If I had a movie
with a character that fits him,

1670
01:19:12,240 --> 01:19:13,640
I would cast him.

1671
01:19:13,720 --> 01:19:14,880
He's very distinct.

1672
01:19:14,960 --> 01:19:17,600
He's distinct.
He definitely has something special.

1673
01:19:17,680 --> 01:19:19,680
Okay, are you ready? Let's keep going.

1674
01:19:19,760 --> 01:19:20,840
Let's go.

1675
01:19:20,920 --> 01:19:23,640
Next up, Manyoo. Open the doors.

1676
01:19:25,040 --> 01:19:26,200
Congratulations.

1677
01:19:27,080 --> 01:19:28,360
Wait, does he not know?

1678
01:19:28,440 --> 01:19:30,400
Why do you look so sad?

1679
01:19:30,480 --> 01:19:32,200
- Why are you sad?
- He probably didn't see it.

1680
01:19:32,280 --> 01:19:33,640
He looks heartbroken.

1681
01:19:33,720 --> 01:19:35,000
He wasn't sure.

1682
01:19:35,080 --> 01:19:36,400
- You didn't raise it clearly.
- I wasn't sure.

1683
01:19:36,480 --> 01:19:38,800
Oh, okay.
I thought you were sad I picked you.

1684
01:19:39,840 --> 01:19:41,280
You scared me.

1685
01:19:41,360 --> 01:19:43,640
<i>I just didn't see</i>
<i>the mentors fighting over me.</i>

1686
01:19:43,720 --> 01:19:46,040
I wanted a moment like that,
but that's all right.

1687
01:19:46,120 --> 01:19:47,920
Mile is my number one anyway.

1688
01:19:48,000 --> 01:19:49,480
Next person, please.

1689
01:19:49,560 --> 01:19:50,640
Rome.

1690
01:19:52,080 --> 01:19:53,680
- Can I have this one?
- I want him.

1691
01:19:53,760 --> 01:19:56,240
- He's so cool. Very unique.
- Can I have him?

1692
01:19:56,320 --> 01:19:58,640
I refuse to lose him again.

1693
01:19:58,720 --> 01:20:00,800
- Hold on, Off.
- Just let me have him.

1694
01:20:00,880 --> 01:20:02,800
- You already have two.
- Okay.

1695
01:20:02,880 --> 01:20:03,880
Open the doors.

1696
01:20:03,960 --> 01:20:05,640
I really want to pick him.

1697
01:20:05,720 --> 01:20:08,840
My first choice was Rome.
And he has to be on my team.

1698
01:20:12,840 --> 01:20:14,360
Calm down. He raised his book.

1699
01:20:14,440 --> 01:20:17,520
Not yet, chill. Don't shake hands yet.

1700
01:20:17,600 --> 01:20:19,440
Not yet. Hold on.

1701
01:20:20,280 --> 01:20:21,480
I loved Rome's photo.

1702
01:20:21,560 --> 01:20:23,720
There's something
very intriguing about him.

1703
01:20:23,800 --> 01:20:24,960
So I wanted him.

1704
01:20:25,040 --> 01:20:29,440
Two teams picked you.
Team Mentor Off and Team Mentor Mile.

1705
01:20:29,520 --> 01:20:31,880
Let's start with Mentor Off.

1706
01:20:31,960 --> 01:20:35,600
I would like to know your goal for today.
What are you looking for?

1707
01:20:35,680 --> 01:20:38,440
Obviously, my first goal is to advance.

1708
01:20:38,520 --> 01:20:41,040
Because I came to this show
to become The Face.

1709
01:20:41,120 --> 01:20:45,560
I also want to develop my career
as a model and actor.

1710
01:20:45,640 --> 01:20:47,480
- To take it further.
- Besides modeling, what else?

1711
01:20:47,560 --> 01:20:50,200
- I want to be an actor.
- Tell me what you want.

1712
01:20:50,280 --> 01:20:51,480
I can give you everything.

1713
01:20:51,560 --> 01:20:53,360
They can give you everything,
and so can I.

1714
01:20:53,440 --> 01:20:55,760
Look, I just got back
from Paris Fashion Week.

1715
01:20:55,840 --> 01:20:58,240
With your charisma, you belong there.

1716
01:20:58,320 --> 01:21:01,720
I've been to Fashion Week.
I love dressing up. I do it every day.

1717
01:21:01,800 --> 01:21:03,720
I don't need anyone to style me.
I style myself.

1718
01:21:03,800 --> 01:21:06,080
Off, I can style myself too.

1719
01:21:06,160 --> 01:21:07,880
- I know that…
- Then why did you speak first?

1720
01:21:08,920 --> 01:21:12,560
I have to get him. I won't back down.
I want him, and I'll get him.

1721
01:21:12,640 --> 01:21:14,480
I saw your IG.
You support Manchester United.

1722
01:21:14,560 --> 01:21:16,640
- They're doing better lately.
- Yes, I'm a fan.

1723
01:21:16,720 --> 01:21:18,120
They are on fire right now.

1724
01:21:18,200 --> 01:21:19,240
- I support--
- Michael Carrick

1725
01:21:19,320 --> 01:21:20,920
is managing them well.

1726
01:21:21,000 --> 01:21:23,200
I've supported them
since Ryan Giggs played against Arsenal.

1727
01:21:23,280 --> 01:21:24,680
Since his rivalry with Arsenal.

1728
01:21:24,760 --> 01:21:26,400
- Oh, wow.
- But he doesn't know.

1729
01:21:26,480 --> 01:21:29,040
If he doesn't know what you like,
he doesn't care about you.

1730
01:21:29,120 --> 01:21:31,600
- Take him to a game?
- Want to go to Old Trafford?

1731
01:21:31,680 --> 01:21:33,560
- Sure.
- Hey, let's go.

1732
01:21:33,640 --> 01:21:35,920
- Let's go. I'm ready.
- Interesting.

1733
01:21:36,000 --> 01:21:37,920
<i>I feel like we have great chemistry.</i>

1734
01:21:38,000 --> 01:21:39,720
I need something like this.

1735
01:21:39,800 --> 01:21:44,000
Being true to himself, wanting to be bold,
and doing what he wants to do.

1736
01:21:44,960 --> 01:21:46,680
I can bring that out of him.

1737
01:21:46,760 --> 01:21:50,760
Excuse me, any advice
from Ananda and Pancake?

1738
01:21:52,840 --> 01:21:54,560
I'll wait.

1739
01:21:54,640 --> 01:21:57,920
I just feel that what's interesting
about Team Off

1740
01:21:58,000 --> 01:22:00,400
is the mindset and personality.

1741
01:22:00,480 --> 01:22:03,880
I think you could learn a lot from him.

1742
01:22:03,960 --> 01:22:05,200
Let's put it this way.

1743
01:22:05,280 --> 01:22:08,120
Team Mile is theory,
but Team Off is mindset.

1744
01:22:08,200 --> 01:22:11,160
I think he can really shape
your perspective.

1745
01:22:11,240 --> 01:22:12,200
<i>I lost confidence.</i>

1746
01:22:12,280 --> 01:22:14,480
<i>Ananda cheered for Off,</i>
<i>I was so discouraged.</i>

1747
01:22:14,560 --> 01:22:16,160
Like, "Oh no, am I going to lose?"

1748
01:22:16,240 --> 01:22:19,840
I turned to look at Rome,
and just thought, "I'm done."

1749
01:22:19,920 --> 01:22:21,600
It's time to choose.

1750
01:22:21,680 --> 01:22:23,960
Rome, which team will you choose?

1751
01:22:24,640 --> 01:22:26,080
Well, I choose…

1752
01:22:33,120 --> 01:22:34,880
Well, I choose…

1753
01:22:34,960 --> 01:22:36,040
Team Off.

1754
01:22:39,040 --> 01:22:42,000
Congratulations to Rome and Mentor Off.

1755
01:22:43,440 --> 01:22:45,440
Give it your all. Keep fighting.

1756
01:22:45,520 --> 01:22:49,000
See you on the show. Team Off is no joke.

1757
01:22:49,080 --> 01:22:50,440
Intimidating.

1758
01:22:50,520 --> 01:22:52,480
So, let me do a quick recap.

1759
01:22:52,560 --> 01:22:56,160
Right now, Team Mile has two members.

1760
01:22:56,240 --> 01:22:59,240
Team Pancake and Ananda has two members.

1761
01:22:59,320 --> 01:23:02,360
And Team Mentor Off has one member.

1762
01:23:02,440 --> 01:23:05,120
All right, next up is Luca.

1763
01:23:08,040 --> 01:23:10,440
Mentors, please raise your modeling books.

1764
01:23:15,200 --> 01:23:17,480
I'm sorry. You are not The Face.

1765
01:23:17,560 --> 01:23:21,200
I like you, but we have a strategy, which…

1766
01:23:21,280 --> 01:23:23,640
I would rather stick to my strategy.

1767
01:23:23,720 --> 01:23:27,440
<i>Luca did nothing wrong.</i>
<i>His only flaw was the language barrier.</i>

1768
01:23:27,520 --> 01:23:31,160
I didn't want to eliminate him
just because he couldn't speak Thai.

1769
01:23:31,240 --> 01:23:32,600
But it was the deciding factor.

1770
01:23:32,680 --> 01:23:34,760
Next up, Man.

1771
01:23:34,840 --> 01:23:35,960
Open the door.

1772
01:23:36,040 --> 01:23:38,520
I'm sorry. You are not The Face.

1773
01:23:38,600 --> 01:23:39,880
Fifa.

1774
01:23:42,800 --> 01:23:43,680
I'm sorry.

1775
01:23:43,760 --> 01:23:45,400
- You are not The Face.
- Thank you.

1776
01:23:46,240 --> 01:23:50,240
<i>I feel bad for the guys who had potential,</i>

1777
01:23:50,320 --> 01:23:52,440
<i>but lost their chance here.</i>

1778
01:23:52,520 --> 01:23:57,840
I respect how tough
and composed all the mentors are.

1779
01:23:57,920 --> 01:23:59,400
It's truly brutal.

1780
01:23:59,480 --> 01:24:01,200
Next person, Rcha.

1781
01:24:05,560 --> 01:24:07,280
- I'm sorry.
- Yes.

1782
01:24:07,360 --> 01:24:08,840
You are not The Face.

1783
01:24:08,920 --> 01:24:11,120
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1784
01:24:12,600 --> 01:24:14,920
- Did he have to walk to the front?
- The further he walks,

1785
01:24:15,000 --> 01:24:16,720
- the less I can look him in the eye.
- Right?

1786
01:24:16,800 --> 01:24:18,560
- It's harder to face.
- Yes.

1787
01:24:18,640 --> 01:24:19,920
<i>I don't know what to do.</i>

1788
01:24:20,000 --> 01:24:22,680
<i>Are we just letting him go?</i>
<i>It happened so fast.</i>

1789
01:24:22,760 --> 01:24:24,080
- Open and close.
- Only raise a book.

1790
01:24:24,160 --> 01:24:25,000
And it's over.

1791
01:24:25,080 --> 01:24:26,520
- He's gone?
- Just like that.

1792
01:24:26,600 --> 01:24:28,560
Next up, Donut.

1793
01:24:31,200 --> 01:24:32,560
Raise it.

1794
01:24:35,960 --> 01:24:37,680
Congratulations, Donut.

1795
01:24:39,480 --> 01:24:42,160
You're in Team Pancake and Ananda.

1796
01:24:43,200 --> 01:24:45,800
My number one pick for the team is Donut.

1797
01:24:45,880 --> 01:24:47,120
He's very surprising.

1798
01:24:47,200 --> 01:24:51,760
He has this sex appeal
that attracts the opposite sex.

1799
01:24:51,840 --> 01:24:54,800
First, thank you for choosing me.

1800
01:24:55,360 --> 01:24:56,800
As for the other two mentors,

1801
01:24:56,880 --> 01:24:58,160
don't regret it later.

1802
01:24:58,240 --> 01:24:59,600
There you go.

1803
01:25:00,360 --> 01:25:01,560
That's the spirit.

1804
01:25:01,640 --> 01:25:02,760
That's enough.

1805
01:25:02,840 --> 01:25:05,520
He's a little ruthless, a little darkness.

1806
01:25:05,600 --> 01:25:08,160
At first, I thought
I would have to fight you for him.

1807
01:25:08,240 --> 01:25:09,960
<i>I was worried others would steal him.</i>

1808
01:25:10,040 --> 01:25:12,840
- No one did. So…
- I'm so happy.

1809
01:25:12,920 --> 01:25:17,120
I didn't have to worry too much about him,
even though I was worried.

1810
01:25:17,200 --> 01:25:20,000
I won't let you two down.

1811
01:25:20,600 --> 01:25:22,880
Let's see the next person.

1812
01:25:22,960 --> 01:25:23,880
Fox.

1813
01:25:24,720 --> 01:25:26,160
I felt a lot of pressure.

1814
01:25:26,240 --> 01:25:29,160
My only hope was
for at least one person to choose me.

1815
01:25:29,240 --> 01:25:31,040
If more than one did,

1816
01:25:31,120 --> 01:25:33,200
I'd be thrilled and that would be a bonus.

1817
01:25:33,280 --> 01:25:34,480
Open the door.

1818
01:25:38,200 --> 01:25:40,320
Congratulations, Fox.

1819
01:25:40,400 --> 01:25:42,200
Congratulations. You're on Team…

1820
01:25:43,840 --> 01:25:46,400
<i>I'm so happy. At least, I made it in.</i>

1821
01:25:46,480 --> 01:25:49,200
But I'm still stressed
about who to choose.

1822
01:25:49,280 --> 01:25:50,400
It's a tough call.

1823
01:25:50,480 --> 01:25:53,320
What do you think?
Didn't you want an energetic mentor?

1824
01:25:53,920 --> 01:25:56,080
- Yes.
- Looking around, it has to be me.

1825
01:25:56,160 --> 01:25:57,720
Last time, you were told that

1826
01:25:57,800 --> 01:26:01,920
before getting an energetic mentor,
you need to be energetic yourself.

1827
01:26:03,440 --> 01:26:05,920
- Didn't she say that?
- Yes, I said it myself.

1828
01:26:06,000 --> 01:26:09,320
So, if you join my team,
you'll definitely get energy.

1829
01:26:09,400 --> 01:26:12,960
Are you actually energetic, Fox?
What do you usually do?

1830
01:26:13,040 --> 01:26:15,440
I normally like playing sports.

1831
01:26:15,520 --> 01:26:19,120
I'm outgoing and active.
I love playing sports.

1832
01:26:19,200 --> 01:26:21,400
But we don't really see
that active side of you.

1833
01:26:22,600 --> 01:26:24,720
In what situation will we see it?

1834
01:26:24,800 --> 01:26:28,120
Maybe in the next Masterclass.

1835
01:26:28,200 --> 01:26:29,840
You should be showing it right now.

1836
01:26:29,920 --> 01:26:33,080
<i>I wanted him when he walked out,</i>
<i>but when he spoke…</i>

1837
01:26:33,160 --> 01:26:35,520
Something was off.
It's the way he used his voice.

1838
01:26:35,600 --> 01:26:37,480
- Or the way he spoke.
- The way he spoke.

1839
01:26:37,560 --> 01:26:39,560
I just think it's not quite right.

1840
01:26:39,640 --> 01:26:41,400
Something is missing.

1841
01:26:41,480 --> 01:26:42,600
Okay, okay.

1842
01:26:43,200 --> 01:26:44,760
I believe you. I can see it.

1843
01:26:44,840 --> 01:26:48,640
I see your dedication.
I see the determination in your eyes.

1844
01:26:48,720 --> 01:26:52,240
Just balance what you do
with the energy you have.

1845
01:26:52,320 --> 01:26:53,480
All right.

1846
01:26:55,080 --> 01:26:56,040
You're suited for Off.

1847
01:26:57,880 --> 01:27:01,400
I'll step aside because I think
you need an energetic person.

1848
01:27:01,480 --> 01:27:03,200
Someone with the power to push you.

1849
01:27:04,000 --> 01:27:05,360
He can do that.

1850
01:27:06,080 --> 01:27:09,160
I'm looking for guys
with diverse characters.

1851
01:27:09,240 --> 01:27:10,800
I want everyone to be like water,

1852
01:27:10,880 --> 01:27:13,880
able to adapt
to various kinds of containers

1853
01:27:13,960 --> 01:27:15,160
and be anything.

1854
01:27:15,240 --> 01:27:19,960
I think everyone here,
from what I've heard…

1855
01:27:20,040 --> 01:27:24,240
Mentor Ananda and Mentor Pancake
are the top favorites here.

1856
01:27:25,000 --> 01:27:29,920
I think the guys who made it here,
the high-level ones,

1857
01:27:30,000 --> 01:27:31,680
the top contenders.

1858
01:27:31,760 --> 01:27:35,120
If they had to choose,
they would definitely go to these two.

1859
01:27:35,200 --> 01:27:36,280
But I think…

1860
01:27:37,760 --> 01:27:42,600
I want to be the standout
in an underdog team,

1861
01:27:42,680 --> 01:27:46,760
and strive to shine as bright
as the leading teams.

1862
01:27:47,560 --> 01:27:50,120
Our team isn't the underdog.
We aren't underdogs.

1863
01:27:50,200 --> 01:27:51,080
No.

1864
01:27:51,160 --> 01:27:53,320
You're making my team
look like an underdog.

1865
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:56,400
You have to appreciate
his competitive spirit.

1866
01:27:56,480 --> 01:28:00,560
I want to join your team
and push you to the elite level.

1867
01:28:00,640 --> 01:28:03,920
Okay, fine. Push me. Come push me.

1868
01:28:04,000 --> 01:28:05,800
Right now. Bring it on.

1869
01:28:06,960 --> 01:28:08,960
You'll make great teammates.
I believe that.

1870
01:28:09,040 --> 01:28:09,920
Thank you.

1871
01:28:10,840 --> 01:28:14,640
Hey, if we train Fox well,
he'll be cool and handsome.

1872
01:28:14,720 --> 01:28:16,080
He'll be able to do many things.

1873
01:28:16,160 --> 01:28:18,000
I'll do my absolute best.

1874
01:28:18,080 --> 01:28:22,320
I'll win everyone's hearts too.

1875
01:28:22,400 --> 01:28:24,960
<i>You would rather be the head of a dog</i>
<i>than the tail of a dragon.</i>

1876
01:28:25,040 --> 01:28:26,800
Off's underdog team.

1877
01:28:26,880 --> 01:28:29,400
Okay, the next person. Jacob.

1878
01:28:31,760 --> 01:28:34,160
Wow, he's handsome.

1879
01:28:34,240 --> 01:28:35,360
Open the door.

1880
01:28:38,320 --> 01:28:39,600
Congratulations.

1881
01:28:39,680 --> 01:28:44,680
I'm a bit sad that Mentor Pancake,
Ananda, and Off didn't pick me.

1882
01:28:44,760 --> 01:28:46,760
I almost cried.

1883
01:28:47,280 --> 01:28:48,520
But it's okay.

1884
01:28:48,600 --> 01:28:51,560
Being chosen by one mentor
makes me very happy.

1885
01:28:51,640 --> 01:28:53,320
Next person. Mew.

1886
01:28:55,440 --> 01:28:56,520
Wow, Mew.

1887
01:28:57,880 --> 01:28:59,280
Come join my team.

1888
01:28:59,360 --> 01:29:00,880
Open the door.

1889
01:29:02,240 --> 01:29:04,360
Congratulations, Mew.

1890
01:29:05,800 --> 01:29:08,600
- You're on Mentor Off's team.
- You were my first choice.

1891
01:29:11,080 --> 01:29:14,040
I'm happy. You look like a great fit.
Nobody can steal him from me.

1892
01:29:14,120 --> 01:29:17,240
I'm really glad to have Mew on my team.

1893
01:29:17,320 --> 01:29:19,560
The other two teams that didn't pick me?

1894
01:29:20,800 --> 01:29:21,880
Watch out.

1895
01:29:21,960 --> 01:29:23,200
And now,

1896
01:29:23,760 --> 01:29:26,000
every mentor only has one spot left.

1897
01:29:26,080 --> 01:29:27,440
Time to decide.

1898
01:29:27,520 --> 01:29:30,600
Okay, if you're ready,
let's meet the next person.

1899
01:29:30,680 --> 01:29:32,160
The next person is

1900
01:29:32,240 --> 01:29:33,200
Maxed.

1901
01:29:37,960 --> 01:29:40,640
I'm sorry. You're not The Face yet.

1902
01:29:43,760 --> 01:29:47,360
I feel bad for Maxed. We love Maxed.

1903
01:29:47,440 --> 01:29:49,200
We wanted Maxed to advance.

1904
01:29:49,280 --> 01:29:53,520
But in the end, Maxed just
isn't strong enough for this yet.

1905
01:29:54,120 --> 01:29:55,040
PP.

1906
01:29:57,400 --> 01:29:59,120
Please raise your modeling books.

1907
01:30:00,440 --> 01:30:01,760
- You're not taking him, Mile?
- Hey.

1908
01:30:01,840 --> 01:30:03,120
Go on, open the door.

1909
01:30:04,160 --> 01:30:05,360
I knew it.

1910
01:30:05,440 --> 01:30:06,440
He made me do it.

1911
01:30:06,520 --> 01:30:08,000
I knew it.

1912
01:30:08,080 --> 01:30:09,560
You can open the door.

1913
01:30:09,640 --> 01:30:10,880
I really stuck to the plan.

1914
01:30:10,960 --> 01:30:12,440
- Hello.
- Hello.

1915
01:30:12,520 --> 01:30:13,640
Hello.

1916
01:30:13,720 --> 01:30:15,120
The Journalism and Mass Comm guys
are handsome.

1917
01:30:15,200 --> 01:30:18,040
Did you ever think two teams
would pick you?

1918
01:30:18,120 --> 01:30:21,000
Not at all. I'm really excited.

1919
01:30:21,080 --> 01:30:22,480
When the door opened,

1920
01:30:22,560 --> 01:30:26,120
and I saw two mentors
holding up the modeling books,

1921
01:30:26,200 --> 01:30:29,040
I was pretty shocked.

1922
01:30:29,120 --> 01:30:34,120
But I like him.
I think he has a lot of unique charm.

1923
01:30:34,200 --> 01:30:38,800
And I think you have the potential
to be a great actor.

1924
01:30:39,440 --> 01:30:42,600
For some people, the downside is

1925
01:30:42,680 --> 01:30:45,000
their persona is too fixed.

1926
01:30:45,720 --> 01:30:47,560
They're too memorable. But you're like…

1927
01:30:47,640 --> 01:30:49,560
Mentor Mile, do you want to say something?

1928
01:30:49,640 --> 01:30:53,520
- Hold on, I'm almost done.
- Just interrupt him. Don't hold back.

1929
01:30:53,600 --> 01:30:56,680
- Almost done!
- Don't hold back. You've got this.

1930
01:30:56,760 --> 01:30:59,000
- Another unique thing is…
- Pancake grabbed the flower.

1931
01:30:59,080 --> 01:31:02,240
You're incredibly versatile.

1932
01:31:02,320 --> 01:31:04,000
I studied Journalism and Mass Comm too.

1933
01:31:04,080 --> 01:31:06,080
Do you want advice
on achieving good grades?

1934
01:31:06,160 --> 01:31:08,520
Good grades with a flexible work schedule.

1935
01:31:08,600 --> 01:31:09,520
Come on.

1936
01:31:09,600 --> 01:31:11,280
Mile, I have a tree, she has a flower.
You want one?

1937
01:31:11,360 --> 01:31:12,760
Yes.

1938
01:31:12,840 --> 01:31:17,960
<i>I just wanted Mile to fight</i>
<i>because they have two people over there.</i>

1939
01:31:18,040 --> 01:31:20,120
I wanted to support him.
I wanted him to have PP.

1940
01:31:20,200 --> 01:31:24,440
Here, I'll put it down.
Get ready to hand it to PP.

1941
01:31:24,520 --> 01:31:25,880
Get ready to hand it to PP.

1942
01:31:25,960 --> 01:31:27,200
Do you like Ananda a lot?

1943
01:31:27,280 --> 01:31:28,960
- Yes.
- A whole lot, right?

1944
01:31:29,520 --> 01:31:30,880
Yes, since I was a kid.

1945
01:31:30,960 --> 01:31:34,320
He wrote in his profile
that he's a huge fan of Ananda.

1946
01:31:34,400 --> 01:31:35,800
How is Mile supposed to compete with that?

1947
01:31:35,880 --> 01:31:38,680
When I was younger,
I was a huge fan of Ananda too.

1948
01:31:38,760 --> 01:31:41,600
I've liked Ananda
since a ghost rode on his shoulders.

1949
01:31:42,320 --> 01:31:43,360
Since <i>Shutter</i>.

1950
01:31:43,440 --> 01:31:45,240
- <i>Shutter.</i>
- I saw him with his long hair.

1951
01:31:45,320 --> 01:31:46,320
I loved that look.

1952
01:31:46,400 --> 01:31:49,480
Experience-wise,
I can't compete with Ananda.

1953
01:31:49,560 --> 01:31:51,400
Or with anything else he is.

1954
01:31:53,240 --> 01:31:55,400
Can I get Mile on my team?

1955
01:31:56,840 --> 01:31:59,760
I changed my mind, PP.
I'll take Mile on my team instead.

1956
01:31:59,840 --> 01:32:02,640
Here we go, PP,
it's time to make your decision.

1957
01:32:02,720 --> 01:32:06,280
I'm really torn. If I have to choose…

1958
01:32:06,360 --> 01:32:07,320
Tough choice.

1959
01:32:07,400 --> 01:32:09,720
PP, you need to decide now.

1960
01:32:17,120 --> 01:32:19,960
Even though Mile went
to the same school as me…

1961
01:32:21,200 --> 01:32:22,560
Mile, put the tree away.

1962
01:32:22,640 --> 01:32:24,760
Let him finish!

1963
01:32:24,840 --> 01:32:26,200
Listen to him!

1964
01:32:26,280 --> 01:32:29,000
If he starts with "even though,"
bring the tree back.

1965
01:32:29,080 --> 01:32:30,080
Let him finish.

1966
01:32:30,160 --> 01:32:31,200
I'm still in shock.

1967
01:32:31,280 --> 01:32:32,960
PP, "even though" was the end.

1968
01:32:33,040 --> 01:32:34,360
I would like to choose

1969
01:32:34,440 --> 01:32:35,280
Ananda.

1970
01:32:37,480 --> 01:32:42,040
Please root for me.
I'm PP from Team Ananda-Pancake.

1971
01:32:43,960 --> 01:32:48,880
The fraternal bond can't beat
what the heart wants.

1972
01:32:48,960 --> 01:32:52,160
We studied in the same faculty,
but he likes Ananda.

1973
01:32:52,240 --> 01:32:55,040
How am I supposed to compete?
I'm hurt a little.

1974
01:32:55,120 --> 01:33:00,120
That means Team Pancake and Ananda
is now full with four members.

1975
01:33:00,200 --> 01:33:05,280
Now, only Team Mile and Team Off
have one spot left.

1976
01:33:05,360 --> 01:33:09,080
Let's meet our next contestant, Dan.

1977
01:33:14,920 --> 01:33:17,440
I'm sorry, but you are not The Face.

1978
01:33:17,520 --> 01:33:19,360
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1979
01:33:20,240 --> 01:33:22,360
Next up, please welcome Safe.

1980
01:33:25,360 --> 01:33:27,720
I'm sorry, but you are not The Face.

1981
01:33:28,760 --> 01:33:29,800
Please welcome Jimmy.

1982
01:33:33,080 --> 01:33:34,040
Wow, great photo.

1983
01:33:34,120 --> 01:33:35,840
Mentors, you can make your decisions now.

1984
01:33:38,120 --> 01:33:39,760
- Open the door.
- Damn, really?

1985
01:33:43,720 --> 01:33:46,320
I'm sorry, but you are not The Face.

1986
01:33:47,480 --> 01:33:51,680
It's a shame. Of all the eliminated guys,
he's the one I regret losing the most.

1987
01:33:51,760 --> 01:33:53,760
Next up, please welcome Leo.

1988
01:33:58,160 --> 01:34:00,600
If you're ready,
raise your modeling books.

1989
01:34:05,560 --> 01:34:06,840
Yes!

1990
01:34:08,640 --> 01:34:13,800
Mentor Mile chose Leo.
Going with an <i>Oppa </i>is super risky.

1991
01:34:13,880 --> 01:34:16,560
Since he picked Leo,
he'll put Leo to good use.

1992
01:34:16,640 --> 01:34:18,080
Okay, Leo.

1993
01:34:18,160 --> 01:34:20,440
I like him, just worried
about the language barrier.

1994
01:34:20,520 --> 01:34:24,880
But I think we can do it.
Google Translate can handle it.

1995
01:34:28,520 --> 01:34:31,240
Mentor Mile, your team is officially full.

1996
01:34:31,320 --> 01:34:33,720
Now, only Mentor Off's team is left.

1997
01:34:33,800 --> 01:34:35,360
Let's check out the next person.

1998
01:34:35,440 --> 01:34:36,440
Bonus.

1999
01:34:37,040 --> 01:34:39,920
<i>I was the very last one. Number 24.</i>

2000
01:34:40,000 --> 01:34:41,080
My heart was racing.

2001
01:34:41,160 --> 01:34:43,680
I danced for five sets and did push-ups.
I did everything.

2002
01:34:45,840 --> 01:34:47,440
Open the door.

2003
01:34:53,480 --> 01:34:55,120
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

2004
01:34:55,200 --> 01:34:56,800
You're on Mentor Off's team.

2005
01:34:56,880 --> 01:34:58,640
- Thank you, Off.
- Thank you.

2006
01:34:58,720 --> 01:35:01,000
- I was nervous being the last one.
- I was waiting for you.

2007
01:35:01,080 --> 01:35:03,320
<i>I'm so damn glad</i>
<i>the others didn't pick Bonus.</i>

2008
01:35:03,400 --> 01:35:07,160
Because we planned
to pick the last person anyway.

2009
01:35:07,240 --> 01:35:09,320
I felt like you weren't under pressure.

2010
01:35:09,400 --> 01:35:11,040
You came here with your friend.

2011
01:35:11,120 --> 01:35:13,800
And I thought,
this man is pretty easygoing.

2012
01:35:13,880 --> 01:35:16,200
Easy to train. I knew you could do it.

2013
01:35:16,280 --> 01:35:17,240
I felt a bit pressured.

2014
01:35:17,320 --> 01:35:18,760
- But I hid it well.
- Okay.

2015
01:35:18,840 --> 01:35:20,360
Off, I'm starting to regret this.

2016
01:35:20,440 --> 01:35:22,360
It was a good take. A really good one.

2017
01:35:22,440 --> 01:35:24,920
No, I'm just saying.
I might be able to steal him later.

2018
01:35:25,000 --> 01:35:26,360
Oh, you can steal me?

2019
01:35:26,440 --> 01:35:28,080
You'll let him steal you?

2020
01:35:28,160 --> 01:35:29,000
- Are you going to let him?
- Are you leaving me?

2021
01:35:29,080 --> 01:35:30,840
- No, I was just joking.
- Okay.

2022
01:35:32,240 --> 01:35:35,000
<i>I'm a little hurt by Mile.</i>
<i>We made eye contact four or five times.</i>

2023
01:35:35,080 --> 01:35:36,800
But he didn't pick me. It's okay, Mile.

2024
01:35:36,880 --> 01:35:38,080
I'll remember this.

2025
01:35:38,160 --> 01:35:40,480
Off is number one in my heart now.

2026
01:35:41,000 --> 01:35:43,200
I love you, Off.
Love you the most. Love you only.

2027
01:35:43,280 --> 01:35:45,480
Love you always.
Love you twenty-four seven.

2028
01:35:45,560 --> 01:35:48,160
If he had come out earlier,
everyone would've picked him.

2029
01:35:48,240 --> 01:35:50,280
Anyway, congratulations, Bonus.

2030
01:35:50,360 --> 01:35:52,320
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2031
01:35:52,400 --> 01:35:54,680
The other two teams must be regretting it.

2032
01:35:54,760 --> 01:35:57,040
Thinking, "Why didn't I pick him?"

2033
01:35:57,640 --> 01:36:00,120
But I got him. Team Off.

2034
01:36:05,920 --> 01:36:08,760
Now, all three teams
have their four members.

2035
01:36:09,400 --> 01:36:13,360
Today, we are bringing back

2036
01:36:13,440 --> 01:36:16,600
the previously eliminated contestants.

2037
01:36:16,680 --> 01:36:20,080
Chosen by the Master Mentor and the show.

2038
01:36:20,160 --> 01:36:22,560
The ones we still want
to see move forward.

2039
01:36:22,640 --> 01:36:25,240
So, please welcome the three contestants.

2040
01:36:26,000 --> 01:36:27,960
Pom, Wigrom, and Gluf.

2041
01:36:32,000 --> 01:36:33,360
Everyone is looking around.

2042
01:36:33,440 --> 01:36:34,480
Where are they?

2043
01:36:35,120 --> 01:36:36,560
Where are they coming from?

2044
01:36:36,640 --> 01:36:40,280
<i>We had no idea. We couldn't guess</i>
<i>what the Master Mentor…</i>

2045
01:36:40,360 --> 01:36:41,400
<i>would do to us.</i>

2046
01:36:41,480 --> 01:36:44,560
I was worried they'd swap the members
since we already picked our members.

2047
01:36:45,120 --> 01:36:47,000
If they did that, there would be a fight.

2048
01:36:47,080 --> 01:36:49,800
All right, the first person is Pom.

2049
01:36:49,880 --> 01:36:53,560
How do you feel today, Pom,
returning to <i>The Face</i>?

2050
01:36:53,640 --> 01:36:55,160
Why did you decide to come back?

2051
01:36:55,240 --> 01:36:57,560
It feels like I died and was reborn here.

2052
01:36:57,640 --> 01:37:00,360
Since I have this chance,
I'll give it my all.

2053
01:37:00,440 --> 01:37:02,080
That was just the first person.

2054
01:37:02,160 --> 01:37:03,680
The second person is Wigrom.

2055
01:37:04,480 --> 01:37:08,160
A contestant who stands out in music

2056
01:37:08,240 --> 01:37:11,040
with versatile skills
in singing, playing, and dancing.

2057
01:37:11,120 --> 01:37:14,720
Given my personality and my many talents,

2058
01:37:14,800 --> 01:37:18,200
I believe <i>The Face </i>needs someone like me.

2059
01:37:18,280 --> 01:37:20,480
And our third person is Gluf.

2060
01:37:20,560 --> 01:37:22,040
How are you feeling today, Gluf?

2061
01:37:22,120 --> 01:37:23,840
When I got the call,

2062
01:37:23,920 --> 01:37:26,120
I was thrilled to get another chance.

2063
01:37:26,200 --> 01:37:28,640
And I knew I would definitely do my best.

2064
01:37:28,720 --> 01:37:31,120
Everything happened so fast. And…

2065
01:37:31,200 --> 01:37:33,200
I'm just really glad to be here.

2066
01:37:33,920 --> 01:37:37,440
Now, I would like to ask
the mentors of each team…

2067
01:37:37,520 --> 01:37:40,680
are there any eliminated contestants
that you want to bring back?

2068
01:37:41,400 --> 01:37:45,840
Now, every Mentor can choose
whether or not to use this right.

2069
01:37:45,920 --> 01:37:47,320
I don't mind.

2070
01:37:47,400 --> 01:37:51,640
If you already like your team,
you don't have to pick anyone.

2071
01:37:52,240 --> 01:37:53,160
That's fine.

2072
01:37:53,240 --> 01:37:58,480
But you guys will have to convince me
that you really want them.

2073
01:37:58,560 --> 01:38:01,080
You can choose someone
who wasn't your initial target.

2074
01:38:01,160 --> 01:38:03,880
I would've picked Jimmy.
But after seeing Pom, I prefer Pom.

2075
01:38:04,640 --> 01:38:07,440
If I really had to choose one,
I would pick Pom anyway.

2076
01:38:07,520 --> 01:38:10,600
Because Pom is someone
I had my eyes on from the start.

2077
01:38:10,680 --> 01:38:14,720
Mentor Off chooses
not to bring anyone back.

2078
01:38:14,800 --> 01:38:16,200
- Yes.
- Okay.

2079
01:38:16,280 --> 01:38:19,240
Mentor Ananda and Mentor Pancake,
who do you choose to bring back?

2080
01:38:19,320 --> 01:38:20,160
- None.
- None of them.

2081
01:38:21,240 --> 01:38:23,360
Now, it's just down to Mentor Mile.

2082
01:38:23,440 --> 01:38:26,120
There's one guy I regret missing out on.

2083
01:38:26,200 --> 01:38:28,680
And he's right here, so I'm like… man.

2084
01:38:28,760 --> 01:38:31,440
I wanted Gluf anyway,
so I didn't know what to do.

2085
01:38:31,520 --> 01:38:34,600
- And the reason is if…
- Hey.

2086
01:38:35,200 --> 01:38:38,320
This is why the last person to speak
always has the advantage.

2087
01:38:38,400 --> 01:38:40,800
I felt like I had to get him.

2088
01:38:41,600 --> 01:38:43,720
Started off by making eyes at him.

2089
01:38:44,680 --> 01:38:47,520
He played along.
Once he played along, he was in the bag.

2090
01:38:48,760 --> 01:38:49,800
Before they try to convince you,

2091
01:38:49,880 --> 01:38:53,400
I want to know
which of the three teams you want.

2092
01:38:53,480 --> 01:38:54,760
Could you tell me?

2093
01:38:54,840 --> 01:38:56,600
Let's start with Gluf.

2094
01:38:56,680 --> 01:39:00,440
I don't think I have anyone in mind yet.
It's better if I don't say.

2095
01:39:00,520 --> 01:39:03,280
All right, let's hear from Wigrom.

2096
01:39:03,360 --> 01:39:08,240
I think Mentor Off
is the mentor I'm aiming for.

2097
01:39:08,320 --> 01:39:10,160
And finally, Pom.

2098
01:39:10,240 --> 01:39:12,640
I admire all the mentors.

2099
01:39:12,720 --> 01:39:15,040
I've walked the runway
with Mentor Pancake before.

2100
01:39:15,120 --> 01:39:17,280
I love all of your work.

2101
01:39:17,360 --> 01:39:19,120
If possible, I would choose Off.

2102
01:39:19,200 --> 01:39:21,480
Oh, wow.

2103
01:39:21,560 --> 01:39:23,000
- Off.
- That's unexpected.

2104
01:39:23,080 --> 01:39:25,800
I'm not glad at all.
The power isn't in their hands.

2105
01:39:25,880 --> 01:39:27,600
Oh, wow.

2106
01:39:27,680 --> 01:39:31,320
- That's how the new generation should be.
- It makes him look cool at the end.

2107
01:39:32,840 --> 01:39:34,480
Who do you want?

2108
01:39:34,560 --> 01:39:37,000
How do you want to convince
our Master Mentor?

2109
01:39:37,080 --> 01:39:38,320
This is your chance.

2110
01:39:38,400 --> 01:39:39,400
Mentor Off.

2111
01:39:42,720 --> 01:39:47,040
You probably heard him say

2112
01:39:47,120 --> 01:39:50,400
he wants me to bring out his potential.

2113
01:39:50,480 --> 01:39:54,400
I believe I can do it because
when he made the top 488,

2114
01:39:54,480 --> 01:39:56,640
I remember he was number 311.

2115
01:39:56,720 --> 01:39:58,080
So his return today

2116
01:39:58,160 --> 01:40:00,320
really warms my heart.

2117
01:40:00,400 --> 01:40:03,760
It makes me feel like
this kid deserves a better chance.

2118
01:40:03,840 --> 01:40:05,480
He even changed his look today.

2119
01:40:05,560 --> 01:40:07,320
Honestly, he is shining even more now.

2120
01:40:07,400 --> 01:40:09,480
He can definitely go further.

2121
01:40:09,560 --> 01:40:11,240
You didn't say that earlier.

2122
01:40:11,320 --> 01:40:12,480
I didn't talk to anyone.

2123
01:40:14,440 --> 01:40:15,800
I didn't talk to anyone.

2124
01:40:15,880 --> 01:40:20,320
Team Pancake and Ananda, who do you like?
Who do you want on your team?

2125
01:40:20,400 --> 01:40:22,240
Honestly, I'm happy with all three.

2126
01:40:22,320 --> 01:40:25,720
This is a new opportunity
for both them and us.

2127
01:40:25,800 --> 01:40:29,640
So I think nobody
does it perfectly the first time.

2128
01:40:29,720 --> 01:40:34,720
But we can learn, adapt,
and improve ourselves to do better.

2129
01:40:34,800 --> 01:40:38,000
If the Master Mentor thinks
who we're suited for,

2130
01:40:38,080 --> 01:40:40,000
or who's suited for us,

2131
01:40:40,080 --> 01:40:42,160
I think that might be more challenging.

2132
01:40:43,680 --> 01:40:44,600
Challenging.

2133
01:40:47,640 --> 01:40:48,600
Sounds great. That's okay.

2134
01:40:48,680 --> 01:40:50,760
Speaking last isn't necessarily good.

2135
01:40:50,840 --> 01:40:51,840
You're up last.

2136
01:40:51,920 --> 01:40:53,240
It's your turn.

2137
01:40:53,320 --> 01:40:55,520
You're the last to speak. What do you say?

2138
01:40:55,600 --> 01:41:00,120
Frankly, I still like Gluf.

2139
01:41:00,200 --> 01:41:05,040
So I feel the show
should rightfully send him to my team.

2140
01:41:05,120 --> 01:41:09,200
I think the Master Mentor is reasonable
and has clear principles.

2141
01:41:09,280 --> 01:41:10,840
He won't blindly mix things up

2142
01:41:10,920 --> 01:41:13,520
and match people
who don't want to be matched.

2143
01:41:13,600 --> 01:41:19,000
All right, all mentors have now
convinced the Master Mentor.

2144
01:41:19,080 --> 01:41:22,480
But the final decision
rests with the Master Mentor.

2145
01:41:22,560 --> 01:41:25,760
I feel like everyone today
deserves a great opportunity.

2146
01:41:26,360 --> 01:41:28,960
And this is an opportunity to invite Pom…

2147
01:41:30,400 --> 01:41:31,520
to join…

2148
01:41:32,960 --> 01:41:34,040
Mentor Off.

2149
01:41:34,120 --> 01:41:38,480
Congratulations, Pom.
You're on Mentor Off's team.

2150
01:41:38,560 --> 01:41:40,720
<i>It's truly fulfilling. It's like…</i>

2151
01:41:40,800 --> 01:41:42,640
This is exactly what I planned.

2152
01:41:42,720 --> 01:41:43,720
Wigrom.

2153
01:41:46,680 --> 01:41:49,680
I feel like Wigrom has what it takes.

2154
01:41:50,680 --> 01:41:52,080
Please join Mentor Ananda.

2155
01:41:54,520 --> 01:41:56,440
Wait, give him the flowers first.

2156
01:41:57,160 --> 01:41:58,240
Give him the flower.

2157
01:41:58,320 --> 01:41:59,560
She's keeping the flower.

2158
01:42:01,240 --> 01:42:02,840
I believe it's my destiny.

2159
01:42:06,440 --> 01:42:08,680
This is the flower from Mentor Pancake.

2160
01:42:11,080 --> 01:42:15,320
And finally, Gluf.
You're with Mentor Mile.

2161
01:42:16,920 --> 01:42:18,680
- Hey, let's bring it in.
- Thank you.

2162
01:42:20,120 --> 01:42:21,440
You have to fight hard.

2163
01:42:21,520 --> 01:42:24,040
<i>I definitely won't let Mentor Mile down.</i>

2164
01:42:24,120 --> 01:42:28,320
I'll adapt everything Mentor Mile told me.
I'll definitely improve myself.

2165
01:42:28,400 --> 01:42:30,880
Now, all mentors have full teams.

2166
01:42:30,960 --> 01:42:34,600
Is there anything you would like to say
to the other mentors?

2167
01:42:34,680 --> 01:42:35,640
Mentor Mile.

2168
01:42:35,720 --> 01:42:37,120
Please go easy on me.

2169
01:42:39,160 --> 01:42:41,640
- See?
- I don't buy it.

2170
01:42:41,720 --> 01:42:44,080
This guy is the most terrifying.

2171
01:42:44,160 --> 01:42:46,240
<i>Mile starts with, "Go easy on me"? What?</i>

2172
01:42:46,320 --> 01:42:49,600
Oh, playing the underdog. Come on. No way.

2173
01:42:49,680 --> 01:42:51,640
I'm telling the truth. Honestly.

2174
01:42:52,280 --> 01:42:53,200
<i>Annyeong.</i>

2175
01:42:53,280 --> 01:42:54,640
<i>Kamsahamnida.</i>

2176
01:42:55,840 --> 01:42:57,800
What about Mentor Pancake
and Mentor Ananda?

2177
01:42:57,880 --> 01:42:59,520
Well,

2178
01:42:59,600 --> 01:43:01,200
things are about to get fun.

2179
01:43:01,280 --> 01:43:02,400
Isn't it fun already?

2180
01:43:02,480 --> 01:43:04,640
No, I mean from now on,

2181
01:43:05,280 --> 01:43:08,800
the real game begins. I'm quite excited.

2182
01:43:09,920 --> 01:43:11,040
Mentor Pancake.

2183
01:43:13,520 --> 01:43:16,760
Don't let your guard down.
I'm not as kind as I look.

2184
01:43:16,840 --> 01:43:18,600
I've been playing the game from the start.

2185
01:43:18,680 --> 01:43:20,640
- They think we never started?
- Right.

2186
01:43:20,720 --> 01:43:22,360
Don't let your guard down either, Pan.

2187
01:43:23,480 --> 01:43:25,560
The others aren't easy targets either.

2188
01:43:25,640 --> 01:43:27,680
And finally, Mentor Off?

2189
01:43:27,760 --> 01:43:29,720
Okay, it's a war from now on.

2190
01:43:29,800 --> 01:43:33,560
Plan your attacks carefully.
I'll handle the defense.

2191
01:43:34,400 --> 01:43:37,920
As for how I'll counterattack,
we'll see about that.

2192
01:43:38,000 --> 01:43:40,080
Please go easy on me.

2193
01:43:40,680 --> 01:43:44,600
<i>And now, we have the contestants</i>
<i>for </i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4<i>.</i>

2194
01:43:44,680 --> 01:43:46,320
<i>All 15 of them.</i>

2195
01:43:46,400 --> 01:43:49,520
<i>And the veteran mentor duo,</i>
<i>Pancake and Ananda,</i>

2196
01:43:49,600 --> 01:43:54,080
<i>grabbed PP, an all-rounder</i>
<i>in music and sports.</i>

2197
01:43:54,160 --> 01:43:58,160
<i>Donut, an intense young CEO</i>
<i>and business owner.</i>

2198
01:43:58,240 --> 01:44:01,480
<i>Kimhan, a cool professional model.</i>

2199
01:44:01,560 --> 01:44:04,520
